column1: ON-HOLD | OSF | Wave9.0 | ACC2 | GeteSIMInformation service is not triggering for S2S multi order line update
column41:
While performing New activation of Esim compatible with as shipping order deliver to your own shop flow , We have observed,  GeteSIMInformation request is not triggering for E-SIM with Ship2Store order in case of multiple order line ids.

*Steps to Reproduce:*
 # Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
 # Add more than one E-SIM compatible Package and Proceed to checkout.
 # Select E-SIM in New connection section.
 # Select Shipping order - Delivery to your own shop
 # Submit order and send for VORAS processing
 # Observe OrderLineID is missing in setorder status after BE processing

 

 

*Actual Result:*  GeteSIMInformation request is not triggering for E-SIM

*Expected Result:* GeteSIMInformation request should trigger

 

(Raised the ticket for tracking purpose)

column937:
24/Dec/24 3:22 PM;robert.goebbels@vodafone.com;Hi,

 

we have discussed this defect together with Gaurab from Amdocs in one of the sessions, last week, in which we analysed E2E the expected behaviour and discussed some defects.

Also Waldemar and Michael Heller were involved.

 

1. What I miss in this error description is the EXACT activities, that the agent/tester has done.

my assumption is:  the agent has selected the unsharp sim swap (which is a possibility in Retail, that will disappear with the esim Push Epic, but is still available if the permission for insert sim_serial_number is set (I think)

so..  question:  did indeed the tester select the UNSHARP SIMSWAP?

 

Because:

IF Agent selects UNSHARP SIMSWAP, 

THEN SubmitOrder.SIMCARD = E (as it always was)

and... OGW is triggered to send the emails when SIMCARD =E

(so.. this is not correct)

 

AS AGREED WITH GAURAB :

Amdocs will change/improve the software:

OGW will not only check for SIMCARD = E,  but will also check whether the NEW_SIM_SERIAL_NUMBER is not populated.

only then the emails will be sent;;;
column939:
30/Dec/24 5:25 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;-> did indeed the tester select the UNSHARP SIMSWAP?

Hello [~robert.goebbels@vodafone.com] In both cases, Email is getting triggered, As the parameter SIMSWAP reason is always handed over to OGW with the value VR (Unsharp) even if the agent has selected Sharp (VS) in front end.

Please find below screenshot from submit order request.

!image-2024-12-30-17-19-16-405.png|width=485,height=600!;;;
column940: 30/Dec/24 9:12 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~robert.goebbels@vodafone.com]  please check the comment from Ajay and let us know if anything still unclear ;;;
column941: 08/Jan/25 12:04 PM;gaurav.lanjewar1@vodafone.com;Hi [~robert.goebbels@vodafone.com]  could you please check & share your observations.;;;
column942:
13/Jan/25 8:46 PM;robert.goebbels@vodafone.com;So final outcome  (my understanding)

Summary: 
 * works as (wrongly) designed
 * Amdocs will fix this without the need of a Change Request
 ** OGW will not only check:  is SIMTYPE E, in order to trigger the emails, BUT also check if the SIMNumber is empty

 

Details:

RETAIL channel; blocking permissions set:
 * agent must therefore insert SIM number (instead of SIMTYPE) AND
 * agent has possiblity to select Sharp vs unsharp simswap 

Omnius sends in submit Order
 * SIMYPE E, because agent has selected unsharp SIMSWAP (not clear to me, but it looks like Omnius also sends SIMTYPE E, if the agent selected sharp SIMSWAP, if I understand the comments right). 
 * SIMSERIAL number (because Agent has inserted a (physical) SIMnumber 

OGW triggers 5910 and/or 5930 email although the agent has inserted a (physical)  sim number

 

Solution: Even if Omnius sends SIMTYPE E,  OGW must also check, if a SIMNumber is provided  in submitOrder.  if the simnumber is empty, only then trigger the emails 

-->  as aligned with Gaurab some weeks ago

 

 ;;;
column943: 13/Jan/25 9:58 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Thank you [~robert.goebbels@vodafone.com] for detailed overview :) ;;;

column921:
24/Sep/24 12:47 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;from our BA:

We have identified a new gap in ESIMPush epic, at least for me it looks like a solution gap.

Following are the scenarios :
 # ShiptoStore
 # Telesales/Retail
 # VORAS sending us status [VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT] in StOrderStatus (after H/W is handed out), with OmniusOrderID as OGWSubOrderId .

 

Expectation and issue:

 
 # OGW will identify the OGWOrderID using the OmniusOrderID and then subsequently the Subcriber Information to perform the ESIMPush procedure [ GeteSIMInfo + MaintainEID] .
 # Currently this is failing as in the request we don’t have OrderLineID , hence OGW doesn’t know which OrderLine to pick for subscriber information [it will be trickier if more than one OrerLineID associated with the order] to fetch the Subscriber Info to progress further.

 

Please note: VORAS doesn’t have OrderLineID in talesales scenario.

 

We need to discuss together to close the gap.

column611: HF26 is finally deployed now too and version of SOC XSD is back to 04.05
column915:
30/Aug/24 3:42 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;comments from TEMS team:-
We received this  EPSM-SOC-0406.xsd  file  in  OCA.000160779 /OC.000160773  (OPM_430.01.24.00)  and this is installed in PR Env as a part of OCA.


Let me clarify the issue here, Currently IT Env is with BSS44 and IT OPM is currently running with Soc version EPSM-SOC-0406.xsd.
In same way as per last OPM deployment [OCA.000160779 /OC.000160773  (OPM_430.01.24.00) ] on PR Env, the similar Soc version has been deployed EPSM-SOC-0406.xsd.

Now both IT and PR OPM is using the same soc version EPSM-SOC-0406.xsd, But from Soc side only IT Env having the latest version 0406.
PR Soc is still running on version 0405, So since the last deployment on PR OPM the incoming requests are using the latest version 0406 but from Soc side its still has the lower version.

That’s the reason the test cases are stuck at Oms-Warte-Antwort step in PR OPM.
To resolve this issue either PR OPM should be downgraded to version EPSM-SOC-0405.xsd or PR Soc version should be upgraded to 0406.
;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | Nationality field is missing on customer details page for DSL ILS orders
column41:
Nationality field is missing on customer details page for DSL ILS orders

*Steps to Reproduce:*
 # Login to telesales/Retail channel
 # Agent created valid shopping cart for existing customer.
 # Agent reached to Customer detail page 
 # Issue observed

Expected result:  Nationality dropdown should be mandatory input. Without selection Agent can’t proceed to sales flow 

Actual result:  Nationality field is missing on customer details page

Reference :- 

OAF-521 OMNIUS CHCK : As an Agent, I wanted to forcefully captured customer nationality, so that Agent avoid mistakes for wrong nationality, - Vodafone Global Jira
column366: We are unable to select nationality while performing DSL ILS orders on customer page
column611: Working as defined in CR 678
column915:
22/Aug/24 1:14 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;We have checked again CR 678

There was a discussion especially about ILS flows and the feedback from Business was:

At ILS there is no “nationality” field for DSL and cable orders, but there is for mobile. The mandatory field will then be empty in the future, meaning you will have to ask the customer again about his or her nationality.

 

Actually we also discussed if it should not be displayed for Mobile ILS, this was wrong from business perspective. But Thorsten Lehnert decided to not change anything, so Mobile is different than DSL/ Cable.

So from my point of view its not a defect as field is not expected for DSL and Cable ILS;;;

column41:

Steps to Re-Produce :

 # Search the Unitymedia address
 # Proceed the order with any BB tariffs.

 # Once order is moved to Unity backend(RNS/CAMA) then check account is active.

13/Aug/24 2:49 PM;elango.durairaj@vodafone.com;Hi Cable Team [~simon.auch@vodafone.com] ,

We are observing that for Unity Media orders—cable Test1b is not triggering the SetOrderStatus towards OGW.

VKD is not calling order.controller -- > updateOrderProgress and then also not able to trigger “status.orderstatusservice” call which shall trigger On-Hold status and then calls towards fulfillment.

column916: 13/Aug/24 6:53 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;tracked via PST Bug [[PSTBUG-2508] OGW not getting response back from UM once order Active in backend - DE Jira (vodafone.com)|https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PSTBUG-2508];;;
column917:
13/Aug/24 7:51 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Feedback from Philippe from PST team:

The UnityOrderTracker processes batches of weborders and one of the other weborders could not be found under that weborder ID (it might have been deliberately be deleted for testing).

This caused the whole batch to fail and not only that weborder.
We are working on a fix ;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | Regression | DSL offers created with July PCAT are automatically changed with August PCAT Release
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (PR)

Channel: Retail + Telesales

Test offer: 

CS ID: 11721936; OSF Order ID: 1104477 (created on 8th of August, {*}valid for 8 days{*})

 

*+Please note:+* 
 * when creating a new offer with the DSL PCAT August Release (ACC2) and opening the offer on the same environment, the bug does not appear, e. g.:

          1. CS ID: 11730890; OSF Order ID: 1105207 (created on 9th of August)

          2. CS ID: 11747135 (created on 12th of August)
 * when creating a new offer with the DSL PCAT July Release (ACC1) and opening the offer on the same environment, the bug does not appear, e. g.:

          1. CS ID: 11748105; OSF Order ID: 862241 (created on 12th of August)

 

{+}Actual result{+}: DSL offers created with July PCAT are automatically changed with August PCAT Release

 

+Expected result:+ DSL offers created with July PCAT should not be automatically changed with PCAT August Release, because the offers on production should be valid for 14 days

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * create a DSL offer in July Release (DSL 250, DSL 50, DSL 100)
 * e. g.: DSL 50 +c"[GS_DSL_9x30E[br]] 9 x 30 Euro Rabatt auf den Basispreis" + "[GS_DSL_100E[br]] 100 Euro Startguthaben" + "[GS_YOUNG_24x5E[br]] Kunde ist unter 28 Jahre alt (GigaZuhause Young)" ({*}has to be addd manually{*})  - CS ID: 11721936; OSF Order ID: 1104477 (created on 8th of August, {*}valid for 8 days{*})

*-------------------------------------------------------------------------------*

*Please note:* 
 * "[GS_DSL_9x30E[br]] 9 x 30 Euro Rabatt auf den Basispreis" is not valid anymore with the DSL PCAT August Release, instead of the for new activation orders with DSL 50 the promo "[GS_DSL_12x30E[br]] 12 x 30 Euro Rabatt auf den Basispreis" is booked
 * "GS_DSL_100E[br]] 100 Euro Startguthaben" is not valid in DSL PCAT August Release and it should be not booked at all
 * "[GS_YOUNG_24x5E[br]] Kunde ist unter 28 Jahre alt (GigaZuhause Young)" is not bookable in DSL PCAT August Release

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 * make sure that the DSL Augst PCAT Release is deployed on ACC2
 * search for the offer (CS ID): 11721936 
 * select the prospect customer data
 * click on the 3 dots menue and select "Bearbeiten"

– > Checkout is loaded – > *OK*
 * continue with the order until the Order Overview

– >  wrong data is displayed --> *NOT OK*
 # "[GS_DSL_12x30E[br]] 12 x 30 Euro Rabatt auf den" ** is booked instead of "[GS_DSL_9x30E[br]] 9 x 30 Euro Rabatt auf den Basispreis"
 # "[LS_DSLBASECHARGE_2E[br]EOL] Basispreisanteil 2 EUR (monatlich)" is booked instead of "[LS_DSL_SURCHARGE_5E[br]EOL] Basispreisanteil 5 EUR (monatlich)"
 # "[GS_WoWi_5E[br]EOL] Sonder-Rabatt 5 Euro" is booked

 # "[GS_YOUNG_24x5E[br]] Kunde ist unter 28 Jahre alt (GigaZuhause Young)" is missing
 # "[LS_YOUNG_9x5E[br]] Ausgleich Gutschrift Young 1.-9. Monat" is missing

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | Production | SIM Card Type and SIM Serial Number tags are missing in submit order request for Retail channel.
column41:
We have observed that SIM Serial Number tag is missing in submit order logs for mobile retail orders.

Test data: 1099941, 1099949

 

Before deployment working Test data: 1095897
| |

Steps to reproduce:
 # Login to retail channel in acc2
 # select mobile package
 # Add hardware (physical SIM lable) and tariff
 # enter sim number in checkout section
 # submit the order 
 # observe the issue in submit order logs

Expected Result: SIM Card Type and SIM Serial Number tag should be populated in submit order logs

Actual result: SIM Card Type and SIM Serial Number tag is missing in submit order logs

 

Reference story: OS-48719 OMNIUS_UM:As a system, I want to create a new permission "ENABLE_ESIMSERIALNUMBER" so that it is mandatory to enter eSIM SERIALNUMBER during checkout OS-48719 - Vodafone Global Jira

The agent would view a single text box for both eSIM and Physical Serial Number (which is to be populated mandatory to proceed) 

Permission
 * ENABLE_ESIMSERIALNUMBER
column366:
Customer is activated with different SIM Number which is assigned by OGW instead of agent entered SIM Number in checkout.

Remark: Orders are not failing in KIAS -> If SIM Number missing from Omnius, OGW is taking sim numbers from OGW Virtual SIM Pool and sending to KIAS for activation.

This issue is happening only when agent selects Hardware which is having Physical SIM label (PSIM Compatibility) in configurator.

In case of New ACQ with both SIM (PSIM and ESIM) compatibility HW in configurator - SIM Card type and New SIM Serial Number is present in submit order request.

In case of New ACQ with Porting and Physical SIM (PSIM Compatibility) HW in configurator - SIM Card type and New SIM Serial Number is present in submit order request.

In case of New ACQ with Porting and both SIM (PSIM and ESIM) compatibility HW in configurator - SIM Card type and New SIM Serial Number is present in submit order request.

In case of prolongation with Physical SIM (PSIM Compatibility) HW in configurator and keep existing SIM Number - SIM Card type and SIM Serial Number is present in submit order request.

In case of New ACQ, New ACQ with Porting and Prolongation with ESIM Compatibility HW in configurator - SIM Card type and NewSIMSerialNumber/SIMSerialNumber is present in submit order request.
column611:
Issue:
When an agent has the AGENT_ROLE_PERMISSION_ENABLE_ESIMSERIALNUMBER permission, two div blocks with the same ID and name are rendered in the checkout new connection section for the SIM serial number.

Initial Behavior:

One div block (without SIM type selection) is loaded by default when the agent has the AGENT_ROLE_PERMISSION_ENABLE_ESIMSERIALNUMBER permission.
Another div block appears after the physical SIM selection.
Problem:

This issue arises in the case of PSIM hardware selection where the physical SIM type button is automatically selected, resulting in two input boxes with the same ID and name for the SIM serial number.
This duplication leads to an empty value being sent for the SIM serial number.
The issue is handled in JavaScript where we disable the ID and name of the div blocks depending on their visibility.
This ensures that only the visible div block’s input field is active, preventing duplicate IDs and names. 

CN # KIAS2000_CN_18638  for wave9.0 Patch  delivery towards PROD 
OSE :9.19.5-B1
Sandbox: NA
OIL: NA

column1: OSF | ACC2 | OPT | BEW Permissions (SetMarketingPermission call) are not updating in KIAS for Inlife sales and Prolongation orders in Retail channel
column41:
We have observed that BEW Permissions (SetMarketingPermission call) are not updating in KIAS for Inlife sales and Prolongation orders in Retail channel.

Test data:

Omnius order id: 1098537        BAN: 110977351

Omnius order id: 1098689        BAN: 110719326

Omnius order id: 1120675

*Steps to reproduce:*

1. Login to Retail Channel with PA/FI  agent.
2. Load prolongation eligible mobile customer having BEW permission<4
3. Perform Prolongation(VVL)/ Packet Andern

4. Select (hardware &) Tariff
5. Fill necessary details.
6. Submit the order

7. Observe the issue in logs

 

FOR BEW permission customer:

select s.customer_id , s.subscriber_no ,p.bew_version_nr,p.PRM_ID,p.prm_value
from subscriber s,billing_account b ,PERM_PREF p
where s.customer_id = b.ban and b.ban = p.ban
and s.sub_status='A' and b.account_type in('I','S') and
s.tariff_option like 'RED%' and p.bew_version_nr != 4; 

 

*Actual result:* SetMarketingPermissions call is not updating

*Expected Result:* SetMarketingPermissions call should get updated

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2/PR | DSL /FTTH Phase 2 order is going to fulfillment started status after completed success again

While performing below scenario, we have observed that DSL /FTTH order is going to fulfillment started status after completed success again

There is only 1 second difference between ORDER_POSITION_COMPLETE(1286) and ORDER_COMPLETED(1290) *if we are processing order next day*

And {*}OGW is processing ORDER_COMPLETED earlier than ORDER_POSITION_COMPLETE{*}, and hence order goes to fullfillment started status again

column917:
21/Jul/24 1:26 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,

i saw what Marco wrote. but it is the issue.

OGW is picking the status at the same time

!image-2024-07-21-10-52-51-438.png!

these 2 statuses working at the same time. 

in our case the completed success process is finishing 1 second before so you are seeing the push order status completed success first.

InProgress-FulfillmentStarted is finishing 1 second after the completed success, so you will see push order status  InProgress-FulfillmentStarted last.

 

 

!image-2024-07-21-10-56-55-623.png!;;;
column918:
22/Jul/24 7:40 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~ran.farjun1@vodafone.com]  maybe you can detail the scenario bit more in context of CR553 (not the enhancement, but the solution which is already in place)

For every transaction considered for handling, OGW will search for the transactions by OrderID in the subscribe table.
 * If no other entries found, process the current transaction.
 * If +legacy+ timestamp (or its analogue – ts+sequence, like in KIAS) is populated:
 * If younger (by {+}*legacy timestamp*{+}) +processed+ entries found, the order of transactions was violated. SKY ticket should be opened, and the flow suspended until resolution.
 * Else if older (by {+}*legacy timestamp*{+}) +unprocessed+ entries found, pick the earliest unprocessed entry and handle it.

what is our expectation now in the context of this ticket.
The timestamp of the status is not exactly the same, but in between there are just miliseconds. 
So this is not covered by CR553 introducted in wave 7.x?;;;
column919:
22/Jul/24 7:54 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;the issue is that OGW will pick the correct sos from the db, but it will not stop there.

it will not wait until the entire process of InProgress-FulfillmentStarted is finished. 

so in that case InProgress-FulfillmentStarted has an advantage of a few miliseconds, but seems the flow of InProgress-FulfillmentStarted is a bit slower then completed-success.

so what happened is that completed-success is finishing a few miliseconds before and sending push order status.

after a few miliseconds inProgress-FulfillmentStarted is finishing and also send push order status, and because its the last one its reflecting in frontEnd;;;
column922:
23/Jul/24 12:04 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~ran.farjun1@vodafone.com]  thanks for your quick feedback. Means as long as backend is not sending it with more space it will not work.

However, there is no way to control / delay the backend responses so we have to accept the behavior?;;;
column923:
23/Jul/24 12:18 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;right, if there is not a delay of a few seconds currently i dont think ogw can handle without some design change.
but, i think the Kafka solution in 9.1 can maybe help in this situation. ;;;

column366: Without "FulfillmentStarted" status order updated sucess. Archiving process is working fine but we miss the InProgress FulfillmentStarted status
column611:
n the test environments the vkd job that does sends the order states to OSF only runs once or twice an hour (and cannot run significantly faster due to rate limiting by unity).
So if the order is in an non-completed state only a few minutes this can easily happen.
So basically for the UM orders-- it is expected behavior to have this intermediate status of InProgress Fulfillment started to be missed.
column915:
19/Jul/24 7:22 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,

 not sure why its on OGW. cable is not sending the status *InProgress-FulfillmentStarted*;;;

column917: 22/Jul/24 2:01 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;Investigation email sent to Cable team to check for the issue about the missing Fullfillment status;;;
column918: 23/Jul/24 2:18 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;reminder sent to cable team for investigation;;;
column920:
23/Jul/24 3:11 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;How much time was the order in the unity system in a non completed state?
Currently there is simply no guarantee by the vkd systems that a InProgess-FulfillmentStarted update is sent if the order is already in a completed state.

Simplified flow on vkd side:
* there is a cron job that regularily requests the states of non completed orders from unity
* if there was a status change it sends the new state received by unity to osf
If the received order state from unity is completed vkd will sent the order state completed to OSF, no intermediate messages will be added.

This can usually only be observed in test environments as in production orders should be in a non completed state "long enough" in any backend.;;;
column921: 23/Jul/24 3:17 PM;elango.durairaj@vodafone.com;[~simon.auch@vodafone.com] *How much time was the order in the unity system in a non completed state?* – We don't have any fixed timeline for open state once order is triggered from OSF portal, But once order reached to Unitymedia RNS/Cablemaster then minimum order will stay open status 15 to 20 mits for work order closure, sometimes it will take longer time also depends on environment feasibility.  ;;;
column922:
23/Jul/24 4:05 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;As per Cable team 
On the test environments the vkd job that does sends the order states to OSF only runs once or twice an hour (and cannot run significantly faster due to rate limiting by unity).
So if the order is in an non-completed state only a few minutes this can easily happen.
So basically for the UM orders-- it is expected behavior to have this intermediate status of InProgress Fulfillment started  to be missed.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | Regression | when confirming a DSL ILS offer via email a Sky Ticket is created, because c_comfort or c_basic are removed automatically
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (PR)

Channel: Retail + Telesales

Test customer: 001909462287 (DSL 50 and c_comfort in the inventory)

 

{+}Actual result{+}: when confirming a DSL ILS offer via email a Sky Ticket is created, because c_comfort or c_basic are removed automatically 

 

+Expected result:+ when confirming a DSL ILS offer via email no Sky Ticket should be created and c_comfort or c_basic should not be removed, because it is mandatory to have always either c_comfort or c_basic in the inventory

 

*Please note:*
 # this is a production bug
 # for FIBER ILS offers which are conformed via email the bug does not appear, e. g.: customer ID: 001952837335; OSF Order ID: 1093789; Barcode: VDE5602850951
 # for new-activation offers which are confirmed via email, the bug does not appear, e. g.: OSF Order ID: 1093571; Barcode: VDE5602850605

column366: FTTH PHASE2 ACT Flow impacted due to this issue - it will not move to status completed
column611:
When Order completed in Backend system, Backend sent ORDER_COMPLETED and CUSTOMER_CREATED both status at same time with 1 sec difference. 

And while processing those status in OGW, ORDER_COMPLETED status processed early and OGW start remaining fulfillment flow and then CUSTOMER_CREATED Setorderstatus completed due to which again order went to In-Progress status.

Issue was in backend.
column915:
11/Jul/24 11:52 AM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi Satish,

seems like we are getting 2 set order status from FN:

!image-2024-07-11-09-19-59-973.png!

the first is ORDER_COMPLETED, so OGW will complete the order and push the status.

the second  is CUSTOMER_CREATED, according to mapping this is equal to InProgress-FulfillmentStarted.

so OGW will push that latest status it is getting from FN.
you need to check with FN why they are sending this status after ORDER_COMPLETED;;;
column916:
11/Jul/24 1:15 PM;satish.dhere1@vodafone.com;Hello All,

Currently we are checking with FN backend ;;;
column917:
11/Jul/24 2:10 PM;satish.dhere1@vodafone.com;Hello All,

As discussed with Ran ,

When Order completed in Backend system, Backend sent ORDER_COMPLETED and CUSTOMER_CREATED both status at same time with 1 sec difference. 

 

And while processing those status in OGW, ORDER_COMPLETED status processed early and OGW start remaining fulfillment flow and then CUSTOMER_CREATED Setorderstatus completed due to which again order went to In-Progress status.

 

Issue was in backend.;;;
column918: 11/Jul/24 7:31 PM;satish.dhere1@vodafone.com;Reopened to update OSF fix description;;;

column921:
22/Jul/24 7:56 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;Hi [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] , thanks for the reply.

so, did you get that reply in the screenshot after following the steps in the ticket description? Because I am not seeing in that list any internet product yet, but maybe I am misunderstanding the purpose of that picture.

 

The desired behaviour is the following:
 * When any TV Connect is booked (for example, TCM) into the TV package, then the _precondition rules result_ will show that there are some products orderable with the property 'tags' containing '[omnius_technician_needed_no|https://smith.ui.cont.connect-vf.de/products?commit=master&flavour=prod&tagsContained=omnius_technician_needed_yes]' and some with the property 'tags' containing ['omnius_technician_needed_yes|https://smith.ui.cont.connect-vf.de/products?commit=master&flavour=prod&tagsContained=omnius_technician_needed_yes]'. Specifically, these will be 'TECNOKIP' and '1V1' or 'VP0'. But important are these tags that I just mentioned.
 ** Note that these products are _not_ put into the basket, but you need to check if they are _available_ .
 * On the checkout screen, this drop-down menu in the ticket description with the red frame should only be displayed when there is either a product orderable with the  tag '[omnius_technician_needed_no|https://smith.ui.cont.connect-vf.de/products?commit=master&flavour=prod&tagsContained=omnius_technician_needed_yes]' or 'omnius_technician_needed_yes'. If none of them is orderable, then the drop-down menu must not be displayed.
 * The same is true for internet products as well

The problem that needs to be fixed is:
 * When you follow the ticket description (first book TV, then book internet, then immediately go to the checkout), the drop-down menu _does_ appear, even though no product with the tag 'omnius_technician_needed_yes' is orderable.
 * From what we can gather, the problem seems to be that OSF decides if it wants to display the drop-down menu for TV when it is in the TV package, but not again later in the internet package (and vice versa).
 * So, what happens is:
 ** you book some TV Connect in the TV package ---> OSF checks for products with the tag 'omnius_technician_needed_yes/no', correctly finds that they are orderable, and stores the decision to display the drop-down menu for TV later in the checkout
 ** then you go to the internet package and select some internet tariff ----> now, with both TV _and_ KIP selected, no products with the tag are available anymore, and OSF correctly concludes to not show the drop-down menu for KIP later in the checkout. {+}But it does not update the stored decision for TV{+}, and will still display it later on.
 * -> What we need to be fixed is that OSF updates this _show-drop-down-menu-or-not_ decision both for TV and internet every time the rules are run, not only when the corresponing package – TV or internet – is currently open.

I hope this helps with what to look for. If you have any more questions, I will help the best I can.;;;

column41:
Test data:

Channel: Retail + Telesales

OSE version: v9.19.2-BB1 2024-07-01 08:35 |07-09|03-03

Cable PCAT version: V2390_2024_07_00_076 

*{color:#172b4d}Please note:{color} when booking KIP (Broadvision) + TV, the technician option for KIP is not displayed - > OK*

*!image-2024-07-09-13-42-35-571.png!*

 

*Expected result corresponding to the requirement: [https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PORPDT-345]*

*When booking KIP + TV OR TV + KIP:*
 # *the Access Details for TV should not be displayed*
 # *the Access Details for KIP should be displayed but without the technician option*

 

{+}Actual result{+}: when booking 1st KIP (not Broadvision) and then TV, the technician option for KIP is displayed

+Expected result:+ when booking 1st KIP (not Broadvision) and then TV, the technician option for KIP should NOT be displayed

 

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * login to ACC2
 * search for a Cable address, e. g.: Hagelstangestr. 30, 81927 München
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"
 * select any KIP tariff ({*}NOT{*} {*}Broadvicion{*}), e. g.: a business tariff "[23C:24M] Red Business Internet 300 Cable netto 49,90 €"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel TV"
 * select any TV tariff, e. g.: "[CGTH006] Vodafone GigaTV Home Cable - 6 Monate 9,99€, danach 14,99€"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * enter the customer data and click on the button "Weiter"

- > the technician option for KIP is displayed - > *NOT OK*

column915:
09/Jul/24 5:15 PM;natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com;Analysis on PCAT side was done by [~tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com] :

Hi, Ariadne,

{*}{color:#de350b}yes, I can confirm that in any case where we book KIP + TV (no matter if Broadvision or not, no matter which order we book it in), no technician section should be shown{color}{*}. 

The reason why this fails is as I tried to point out in my comment below. It really is pretty confusing, I apologize for that. I had a call with Natasa where I explained the problem, because it really is a bit hard to grasp.

So again in case of Broadvision what happens is:
 - [In the KIP package] KIP is booked, TV Connect is added because of Broadvision ---> OSF understands that no section for KIP should be shown because KIP + TV is booked and remembers that

 - [In the TV package] TV Digital is booked ---> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked

==> no KIP or TV technician section is shown

In case of Not-Broadvision:
 - [In the KIP package] Only KIP is booked, but not TV yet ----> OSF supposes that a technician section should be shown for KIP (because only KIP is booked) and remembers that
 - [In the TV package] TV Digital + TV Connect is booked ----> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked, but doesn't update the reasoning for KIP

==> technician section is shown for KIP, but not for TV;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | OS-9063 | While performing two D2C owner change in one order scenario orders failing with birthdate missmatch in the markets error
column41:
Hello,

While performing two D2C owner change in one order scenario getting birthdate missmatch in the markets error

Test data: 
OGW: 2845549

Debit msisdn: GSM1721461111, GSM15203801982

Pre-requisite: Agent has permission DEBIT_TO_CREDIT permission

*Steps to reproduce:*

*Configurator*:
1. Login to Retail Channel.
2. Select mobile package
3. Select hardware & Tariff
4. Fill necessary details.
5. Do check the D2COC check box
6. Enter debit MSISDN and click on validation button
7. Submit the order

Currently there are two subscribers which agent is converting to credit market from Debit.
But when OGW is calling activate subscriber request, OGW is sending 1st subscriber details along with second subscriber date of birth, first name and last name, Also second subscriber is missing in request.

Here the expectation is OGW should send same customer subscriber number with his linked date of birth and fistname, lastname details.
column366: In case of order contains two or more mobile packages with D2C owner change, order will be failed.
column611:
Code Fix
Sending correct birthDate after searching the correct order line

we think we are sending the birth date of the second order line instead of the first.

i dont think we need to send both of them in the same request.

 

this is what we are currently sending:

<mfs1:debitBirthDate>1988-05-09</mfs1:debitBirthDate>
<mfs1:debitFirstName>Ekgwdfrv</mfs1:debitFirstName>
<mfs1:debitLastName1>Zcwxuc</mfs1:debitLastName1>

this is what we think we should send:

<mfs1:debitBirthDate>1947-05-19</mfs1:debitBirthDate>

09/Jul/24 5:04 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Feedback from EAI Team

this is a missing validation in EAI. If KIAS does not allow more than 20 SOCs, EAI has to limit the input otherwise we risk overwriting existing values and causing an unexpected behavior. I will issue a low prio ticket.;;;
column917:
10/Jul/24 4:26 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Update after some call today from EAI team: 

Andreas Heuer opens an EAI PRT ticket allowing the request only if the maximum number of SOCs in input does not exceed 20.

The KIAS Z_PRT00146148A is downgraded to P3 and set to “Documentation ticket”. Please modify the CSM494 interface description to explicitly state that the calling system must ensure that no more than 20 SOCs are in the input

 

Additional info: We check with PCAT team if any requirement with more than 20SOCs is planned, as it will not work E2E;;;

Barcode ID: VDE5602844098, VDE5602844085

 

*Steps to reproduce:*

column919:
10/Jul/24 6:57 PM;sandeepkumar.pradhan@vodafone.com;Hi All,

{*}Why issue Occurred{*}: Since all the 3 field for CustomerDataHUB Solution1 Settings and CustomerDataHUB Settings  such as

CustomerDataHUB Solution1 Settings 
1)Central Search ES Interfaces Enabled

CustomerDataHUB Settings
1)Legacy search and MRT Enabled
2)Enable CDH Interface
are set to "Yes" which breaks the API flow in current OSE build  which is not the case in ACC1 or PROD
in both these environment at least one of the them or all are set as "NO" where both customer search and Installed base working fine (for PRODUCTION all filed set as NO)


{*}Action plan{*}: we need to work with Vodafone design team to understand on what criteria these all filed need to switch on (Set as yes) after that or parallelly we need look from OSE prospective how we can handle these API irrespective of setting (all 3 set to YES or all 3 set to NO(working condition) or partial set of YES and NO (working condition))
 

Also PROD and ACC2 are almost equal we should ensure that ACC2 setting always same that of PROD else conf change leads to issue like this , Do understand that tACC2 setting can be change too for testing but it has to be known to an extent;;;
column920:
11/Jul/24 12:02 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~sandeepkumar.pradhan@vodafone.com]  the settings on ACC and in PROD will never be exactly same, as we are always testing future topics in ACC which might not be live yet.
However, for these Fusion C switches we had topics in scope for different releases, so the functionality itself is live since a long time but with a technical go live.

1)[OS-8975] SOL0 - Search & display customer with product(s) mastered in solstice - Vodafone Global Jira -> implemented with Wave 7.0, tested with Wave 7.1  

2) [OS-11283] SOL1SE32 - Extending the OSF Search for Solstice Customers - Vodafone Global Jira -> initially implemented with Wave 7.2, because of needed enhancement tested again with Wave 9.0 

We are not having any new functionality, the switches are there since years. 
To retest your TechM fix for OS-56961 of course all switches had to be YES and in release Wave 9.0 they have been on YES in general most of the time, as OS-11283 was part of Wave 9.0 and tested by Fusion C team.

As ACC1 was used for Wave 8.2 of course ACC1 was different, as there only OS-8975 was live already (therefore only one switch was enabled) 

And as its technically live, Fusion C team can decide at any time to switch it ON in production. Its like any other technical go live, where functionaly is enabled in ACC but not yet in production.;;;

11/Jul/24 7:56 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com]  based on the latest calls e have the following findings for Retail BEW and unitymedia in general

1) New customer, Retail, order + BEW -> Backend receives and stores BEW correctly

2) Existing customer, Retail, order + BEW -> Backend receives and stores BEW correctly

3) Existing customer, Retail, BEW only ->{color:#de350b} *Backend receives and stores BEW correctly? Please confirm this*
{color:#172b4d}What is wrong in all cases -> Frontend OSF is not able to retrieve the right BEW settings. So if BEW was updated in UNitymedia backend, Frontend is not reflecting this. It still looks like no BEW is set{color} ** 
{color:#172b4d}We will also compare the same for VKD, how Retrievecustomerinfo Mode 3 related to BEW permissions is looking like{color}{color};;;
column925:
12/Jul/24 7:08 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com]  the ticket itself is only for Unitymedia, so for VKD its not a problem and no ticket reported.

We still need to document here, if the Existing customer, Retail, BEW only for Unitymedia is reaching the backend as ticket says 

_*{color:#de350b}BEW version is not updating in Unity Backend{color}* and BEW Erfassen is enable even after update the version._

 

At the moment we assume, BEW version is getting updated in Unity backend, but we cannot retrieve the GetPermissions because its not giving back the correct version 
Unitymedia is handling permissions with Version 2, OGW expecting Version  4 and for retrieval of existing permissions we get Version 0.

Needs to be checked with responsible person from MinervaAdapter (VKD side);;;
column926: 17/Jul/24 2:34 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;No progress yet as we did not identify the responsible person who can help with Minerva Adapter VKD ;;;
column927:
18/Jul/24 9:28 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;I have enclosed the latest discussion.
As per latest analysis this problem is related to the way back from Unitymedia via Minerva Adapter VKD to OGW

{color:#de350b}*OK:*{color} OGW version 4 -> Minerva Adapter maps Version 4 from the VKD request into Version 2 for the request to UME/VFW -> UME/VFW is storing Version 2 correctly in Mood and showing right entries in RNS for the customer 

{color:#00875a}*Not OK*{color}: Now when we open the customer who has given BEW again in OSF, we expect that the stored BEW is taken and we are not asked to capture BEW again. Problem: For this get_permission Call we are receiving version 0 for the mentioned scenarios and we cannot map this version to our valid Version 4 (not OK)

{+}*Gap*{+}: We need a Mapping: UME/VFW is sending back Version 2 to Minerva Adapter-> Minerva Adapter maps Version 2 to Version 4 if getpermission request is coming from OGW

 

I have shared the feedback also with Jörg Trierweiler, Thomas Schneider, Andreas Baldermann and few more people to verify.
This is a general topic and not specifically related to BEW only Retail Epic
Waiting for feedback about possible next steps;;;

column934:
14/Aug/24 1:46 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;As Discussed, post the OGW changes related to FastSearch flow-- we have the below current valid behavior:
Below Flow flow will be always triggered until OGW keeps receiving Intermediate status as "Customer created" from DSL backend
DSL--> OGW will call In progress (Customer created) status
OGW-->OneDMS Will call: In Progress Doc-Archiving(internally it will call FastSearch/Save Document
As per the BAU flow from DSL backend systems-- they will be sending the above intermediate status of customer created--multiple times to keep updating OGW about customer creation until they complete the order and send ORDER_COMPLETED status to OGW.
OGW will stop calling InProgress Doc Archiving status as soon as it receives the updated status as "ORDER_COMPLETED"
Bottomline: Multiple In Progress Doc Archiving status call are expected from OGW -->OneDMS --as DSL backend will be sending this intermediate status to OGW until the Order is getting completed at backend.;;;

column1: OSF | ACC2 | Wave 9.0 | CR791 | Proper status is not being handled in OGW results in not generating the Marsh file
column41:
The marsh file is getting generated when OGW is sending an internal status completed success.

But in some special cases for *Mobile* and when channel is {*}Telesales{*}(s.1 & 2) the Marsh files are not generated, because OGW is not sending this completed success.

The status is updated  accordingly and push it to Omnius but the internal call is not getting triggered:

1.        simCard = E

           orderLineIncludesHardware = false

           multiSIMADDExists = true and multiSIMADDOnlyESimExists = true.

2.        simCard = E

           orderLineIncludesHardware = false

           multiSIMADDExists = false

 

 

 

We observed issue that Marsh file is not getting generated with any order where some of the orders are not getting the correct completed success status

 

issue observed while performing the below flow

OSF | Wave 8.2.2 |OAF-710|TC_18 Perform New activation and Verify that that agent able to proceed with adding 3  mobile Contracts in the Telesales channel

 

Steps to reproduce:

1) Login to telesales and configure the mobile package

2) configure mobile packages and take Insurance Vodafone cover or vodafone cover plus

3) proceed to checkout and generate documents

4) submit the order

5) check for the sky ticket and conclude with either Success resume or Continue with Next Step

6) check for the Marsh file

 

Expected Result:

All the orders placed in telesales with Psim or Esim should properly be able to conclude and should get Marsh file

 

Actual Result:

Currently as per the understanding orders not getting handled properly if Esim is selecting in the flow and results in not getting Marsh file

Note:  Orders gets failed for any reasons and generates SKY ticket will not be able to generate Marsh file

 

Order details:

Time: 9:10 AM

ID: 1084501

column1: OSF | Wave9.0 | ACC2 | OS-10435 | Incorrect "CustBirthDate" format is being sent in SendDocumentRequest for E-SIM Activation 5930 Email.
column41:
While performing Mobile contract prolongation flow in Retail channel with eSIM push functionality, We have observed, Incorrect "CustBirthDate" format is being sent in SendDocumentRequest for E-SIM Activation 5930 Email.

5930 actually is not only an Email, but also contains 2 attachments

5940:  QRCODE  of the activationcode

5950: PIN

To open both this attached we required password as Birthdate but its accepting password in this format -YYYYMMDD but as mentioned in 5930 mail format should be ddmmyyyy

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*
1. Login to Omnius as Retail/Telesales channel.
2. Search existing Mobile customer which is eligible for Prolongation/New Activation/D2C.
3. Add E-SIM compatible Hardware and Proceed to checkout.
4. Select E-SIM in New connection section.
5. Submit order and verify SendDocumentRequest is generated after the prolongation flow completed from KIAS.

Test Data :  Omnius ID: 1084029
OGW ID: 2835977

*Actual:* Incorrect "CustBirthDate" format - is being sent in SendDocumentRequest for E-SIM Activation 5930 Email.
Incorrect :<ns5:Element key="CustBirthDate">
<ns4:Value>
<ns4:Zeichenkette>19851104</ns4:Zeichenkette>

*Expected:* CustBirthDate format should be ddmmyyyy

!image-2024-06-25-14-14-23-920.png|width=453,height=66!

YYYYMMDD

I assume for all other we leave birth date as it is or its not relevant at all for the other documents

column1: OSF | Wave9.0 | ACC2 | OS-10434 | OGW is sending Activation code value without prefix in SendDocumentRequest for 5930 email.
column41:
While performing Mobile contract prolongation flow in Retail channel with eSIM push functionality, We have observed, OGW is sending Activation code value without prefix in SendDocumentRequest for 5930 email.
 
*Steps to Reproduce:*
 
1. Login to Omnius as Retail/Telesales channel.
2. Search existing Mobile customer which is eligible for Prolongation.
3. Add E-SIM compatible Hardware and Proceed to checkout.
4. Select E-SIM in New connection section.
5. Submit order and verify SendDocumentRequest is generated after the prolongation flow completed from KIAS.
 
*Actual:* OGW is sending Activation code value without prefix in SendDocumentRequest for 5930 email.
 
*Expected:*  # OGW needs to call GeteSimInformation API as described in OS-49735 to fetch the relevant information to use in SendDocument API.
 * 
 ** *Special handling for ActivationCode* - LPA+:+$(ActivationCode) , we need to add a prefix as "LPA:" before the ActivationCode before sending it to OM.

*Test Data:*

2831582

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | PR/ACC2 | OGW showing Push Order Status as InProgress-FulfillmentStarted after Completed-Success for DSL Komfort to Basic tariff change orders
column41:
While performing below scenario, we have observed that OGW showing Push Order Status as InProgress-FulfillmentStarted after Completed-Success for DSL Komfort to Basic tariff change orders.

*Scenario:* DSL customer with 3 phone numbers and "c_comfort" does a tariff change to GPON and changes to "c_basic"

*Test Data:*

Barcode: VDE5602828224

OGW Order id : 2828224

*Env* - PR/ ACC2

*Step to reproduce:*

1)Login to Omnius with Telesales/Retail channel

2)Load existing DSL customer and perform Komfort to Basic tariff change

3)Submit order

4)Perform Backend Process in OPM

5)Check order status after COM database

6)Verify InProgress-FulfillmentStarted after Completed-Success

*Actual Result:* OGW showing Push Order Status as InProgress-FulfillmentStarted after Completed-Success.

*Expected Result:* OGW should show Push Order Status as Completed-Success.

column1: OSF | ACC2 | Wave 9.0 | CR650 | Additional Vodafone Cover Plus insurance options are visible in configurator.

4. Observed that additional Insurance product options are  visible in configurator.

column1: OSF | Wave9.0 | ACC2 | Fixnet Multimapper behaviour concerning basketAction CHANGE
column41:
Please analyse why we have a difference in the behaviour of the multimapper concerning the basketAction CHANGE

Current result::
On ACC2 environment the multimapper entries with basketAction CHANGE are not triggered any longer whereas the same is still working on the ACC1

Expected result:
We need a clear statement which basket actions can be used for mutually exclusive category or subpackage with a cardinality 1..1

 

Discussion via email:

Hi Rahul,

 

as just discussed in the call:

Was there any change in the last time on Omnius side concerning the basket action change?

Because we have a different behaviour on ACC1 (Wave 9.0) and ACC2 (Wave 9.1)

 

I used the same customer and performed the same tariff change (which includes a change from accessTechnology IP Bitstream to L2-BSA VDSL)

 

But however on the ACC1 a multimapper rule is triggered, but on ACC2 not.

 

I’m talking about this one

            <Attribute>

                <BasketAction>change</BasketAction>

                <AttributeCode>access@ID</AttributeCode>

                <AttributeValue>ACCESS-EE1</AttributeValue>

                <AttributeAdditionalValue>/accesses/ipBitstream</AttributeAdditionalValue>

                <Direction>out</Direction>

                <AttributeAction>overwrite</AttributeAction>

                <ProcessContexts>

                    <ProcessContext>ILSBLU</ProcessContext>

                </ProcessContexts>

                <SourceConditions>

                    <Aggregator>any</Aggregator>

                    <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>

                    <ConditionName>Products in Category IPB in the Installed BaseXXX_7381</ConditionName>

                    <SourceCondition>

                        <Type>order.containsInstallBaseProductInCategoryId</Type>

                        <Params>

                            <Param name="categoryID">FN143</Param>

                        </Params>

                        <Operator>is</Operator>

                        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>

                    </SourceCondition>

                    <SourceCondition>

                        <Type>order.packageContainedInstalledBaseProductInCategoryId</Type>

                        <Params>

                            <Param name="categoryID">FN143</Param>

                        </Params>

                        <Operator>is</Operator>

                        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>

                    </SourceCondition>

                    <SourceCondition>

                        <Type>order.packageContainedInstalledBaseProduct</Type>

                        <Params>

                            <Param name="SKU">FTTH-L2-BSA-DTAG</Param>

                        </Params>

                        <Operator>is</Operator>

                        <ConditionValue>true</ConditionValue>

                    </SourceCondition>

                </SourceConditions>

            </Attribute>

 

The SKU IP-Bistream is part of category FN143 so it should be evaluated to true
|sku|external_category_id|
|IP-Bitstream|FN143|
|IP-Bitstream VDSL|FN143|
|L2-BSA VDSL|FN143|

root specific error log

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | Getting Asb value mismatch for DSL Test Data creation on FTTH Address
column41:
*Issue:* Getting error while doing OPM for DSL orders on DGW address.

*Test Data:*

VDE5602822120

*Error:*

"ORA-20002: NDS-00009: Dokumentationsfehler: Es konnte kein DSLAM Device ermittelt werden, welches zum HVt "HVT/04976/1" re"lationiert ist."

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to omnius
 # Search for DGW address
 # Take the DSL plan and Weiter
 # Submit the order.
 # Do OPM processing.

*Expected Result:* Order should move ahead without any error.

*Actual Result:* Getting below mentioned error while doing OPM.

"ORA-20002: NDS-00009: Dokumentationsfehler: Es konnte kein DSLAM Device ermittelt werden, welches zum HVt "HVT/04976/1" re"lationiert ist.

 

Note: {color:#ff0000}*"HVT/04976/1" . Here ASB is sending "1" value instead of 122. that's why crammer is throwing an error. Hence, VFP change is needed here.*{color}

column1: OSF Wave 9.0 ACC2 Servicepauschale Gerätetausch shouldn't be shown on Contract Summary
column41:
Test data:

Browser: microsoft edge
Environment: ACC2
Channel: Telesales + Retail

Steps to reproduce the issue:
 - Enter customer 931951572 (existing customer VKD with homebox2 in inventory makes device change without tariff change)
 - ILS Flow "Paket ändern"
 - Select existing package: "Kabel Internet & Phone" to see the available options
 - Select option : "[OHH]Option HomeBox (Fritz!Box 6670) 5,99€"
 - Check shopping cart and move to checkout -> see in extended shopping cart that there is no monthly fee of 5,00 Euro for Servicepauschale, its just a one time fee
 - Fill all relevant details in checkout section and move to Contract Summary creation page
 - create and open Contract Summary

ID: 10486670 Stand: 07.06.2024

Current result: Position "Servicepauschale Gerätetausch 5€/month" is displayed on the Contract Summary in section "Monatliche Zahlungen"

!image-2024-06-07-14-37-03-841.png!

Expected result: Position "Servicepauschale Gerätetausch 5€/month" is NOT displayed on the Contract Summary in section "Monatliche Zahlungen".

Shopping cart is correct and not showing any Servicepauschale with a monthly price

Cable Weborder which is transfered to backend is also looking fine.
We compared with different portal ECC and here also CS is working fine, so its only a problem with OSF orders
column366:
Customer will have a wrong contract summary with some amount he does not need to pay. Risk to not get the confirmation for this contract summary. 

At the moment kept with prio 3 as it seems to be specific use case, but if other scenarios will have same issue we have to increase priority.

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | PR | DSL orders are getting stuck at 1280_SEND_CCB in COM after OPM Processing
column41:
DSL orders are stuck at state 1280_SEND_CCB in COM after OPM Processing with no error.

*Steps To Reproduce:*

1) Login To Omnius Retail / Telesales Channel.

2) place ILS Order.

3) Check the Status of the order in COM. It should be 1270.

4) Perform OPM Processing.

5) Once OPM Processing is done check order Status Again in COM.

 

{*}Actual Result{*}: Order stuck at 1280 without any error.

{*}Expected result{*}: Order should Reach to FINAL State in COM.

 

*Test Data:*

VDE5602821305

VDE5602821243

 

!image-2024-06-07-15-22-51-586.png|width=488,height=173!
column366: Orders are not getting final so couldn't complete the E2E testing
column611:
sequence number for CustomerOrderId attribute in PRONL database.

We have corrected the sequence number for CustomerOrderId attribute and restarted the PR CCB Pods
column915: 07/Jun/24 7:14 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~alka.kshirsagar2@vodafone.com]  is this only for ILS flow and for legacy DSL or for all use cases and also FTTH?;;;
column916:
10/Jun/24 1:52 PM;alka.kshirsagar2@vodafone.com;This issue was coming for ILS order in general for DSL PKAT testing.

we will do retest today

 

Comments from TEMS Team:

We have checked the COM and FIF logs for the given barcode but we did not find any error in logs.

We found  issue with sequence number for CustomerOrderId attribute in PRONL database.

We have corrected the sequence number for CustomerOrderId attribute and restarted the PR CCB Pods.

 ;;;

column1: OSF | ACC2 | Wave 9.0 | Hardware (sub) tariffs are not visible in configurator for SOHO RV whereas only SIM only Tariffs are getting visible
column41:
We have observed that in the SOHO  Business RV flow there are no Hardware and Tariff option available to select. Agent is unable to complete the flow

{*}Mobile PCAT version{*}: OPMExport_22362_2024_06_05_16_58.zip

Note: We tried by switching browser and clearing cache getting same issue 

 

Steps to Reproduce:

1) Login retail channel

2) Selected the RV 

3) select HW and check Tariff section.

3) unable to see any hardware (sub) tariffs in configurator whereas only SIM only Tariffs are getting visible

 

 

Actual Result:  Agent is unable to see any Hardware (Sub) Tariff where we only Sim only Tariff in SOHO Buisness RV flow 

Expected Result: Agent should be able to select Hardware and respected Tariff based upon the defined rules and Tariff with respect to HW should also be visible in configurator for SOHO Business RV

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | eSIM Push (part 1) |Zeichenkette value is needs to come from KIAS in GeteSIMInformationResponse
column41:
Our SendDocumentRequest for E-SIM Mail Activation is failing with 'dom:Value' is not complete' exception as Element key="Pin" is sent without Zeichenkette value.

 'Zeichenkette ' value is needs to come from KIAS in GeteSIMInformationResponse and then OGW will map received Pin value in SendDocumentRequest.

 

*Note:* Defect raised for tracking purpose.

column41:
We are performing OS-17584 BEW Retail Epic and observed Signature button(Signature option) is disable for VKD(Cable) and UM(Unity Media) stack.

However, we are able to proceed Mobile and DSL stack.

*Steps to reproduce:*
 # login to retail channel.
 # Search existing customer cable/UM.
 # Retrieve the customer.
 # Click on BEW BEARBEITEN button
 # Verify BEW banner notification
 # Select BEW ERFASSEN
 # Verify new popup window open for BEW and select the (ADV/DEV )checkbox
 # Select DOCUMENT ERSTELLEN.
 # click on drucken.

column366: As Mock is not having BanPartyID data, so if OGW AutoRegisterOnlineUser interface switch to Mock, BanPartyID field is going empty in Fulfillment Request due to which orders are getting failed in WriteMemoRequest (E2E flow).
column611: No Fix Required as BanPartyID is not required for WriteMemo Request anymore.
column915: 05/Jun/24 1:25 PM;gaurav.lanjewar1@vodafone.com;Hi [~ran.farjun1@vodafone.com]  When it will be delivered?;;;
column916: 05/Jun/24 8:01 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~ran.farjun1@vodafone.com]  if we are now only having the same BAN as reply from Autoregisteronlineuser - what happens when we submit the order to backend? Is this causing any issues? ;;;
column917:
05/Jun/24 9:14 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Hi [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com]  [~ran.farjun1@vodafone.com] As discussed with Andreas Knocke, Customer ID (BAN) will be linked to BanPartyID once OGW triggers additionally two more requests towards EAI and then EAI will get response from MINT/KIAS.
 # OnlineUser_001:UpdateOnlineUserRegistrationStatus
 # OnlineUser_001:GetPartyForManagedBusinessObject

And above two services are not yet implemented in OGW/OSF, Therefore, OGW will map LegacyCustomerID as a BAN in WriteMemoRequest instead of BanPartyID.

I think so BanPartyID is not being used in ActivateSubscriberRequest input so it will not cause any issue even if OGW is sending same stub response to Omnius, [~ran.farjun1@vodafone.com]  Please confirm once from your side :);;;
column918:
06/Jun/24 11:30 AM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Yes Ajay,

so im reverting my commit and i think you can close this defect;;;
column919:
06/Jun/24 11:46 AM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com]  just to have it understood completely. 
For our normal testing we do not need to enhance Mock? 
as in ticket OS-56745 its stated: BanPartyID is missing because AutoRegisterOnlineUser is not returning BanPartyID in response, after switching to AutoRegisterOnlineUser interface to real connection and now BanPartyID is received in generate contract response 

 

So if we return to Mock again, it will work for *all cases apart from Memo creation for D2COC* which needs to be fixed independently from our Mock? 

But for this use case we still need to enhance the Mock? To get PartyID back. ;;;
column920:
06/Jun/24 12:13 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Hi [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] 
Yes correct, OGW needs to Map LegacyCustomerID which is coming in SubmitOrderRequest instead of BanPartyID and there is no impact for other scenario (other than D2C owner change), [~ran.farjun1@vodafone.com] Can you please check the use of BanPartyId in Input Request, if it was only applicable for WriteMemo Request, I will close this ticket.;;;
column922: 06/Jun/24 12:33 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Thank you [~ran.farjun1@vodafone.com] for confirmation :) I will close this ticket.;;;

column1: OSF | ACC2 | Wave 9.0 | Regression | Standard Authentication window is displayed instead of the SPIN window if FLEX_AUTHENTICATION and SPIN_AUTHENTICATION are assigned
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2

Channel: Retail + Telesales

Test customer: 906516095 (SPIN: 967138)

 

 

{+}Actual result{+}:  Standard Authentication window is displayed instead of the SPIN window if FLEX_AUTHENTICATION and SPIN_AUTHENTICATION are assigned

+Expected result:+  SPIN window should be displayed if FLEX_AUTHENTICATION and SPIN_AUTHENTICATION are assigned

 

+Steps to reproduce:+

 
 * login with a role where the permissions: "FLEX_AUTHENTICATION" and "SPIN_AUTHENTICATION" are assigned on ACC2
 * search for a Cable customer where an SPIN is assigned: 906516095 

– > masked result is displayed --> *OK*

!image-2024-06-03-21-35-52-567.png!
 * select the customer data

– > 360 view is displayed – > *OK*
 * click on the button "Kunden authentifizieren"

 

– >  the Standard authentication window is displayed – > *NOT OK*

*!image-2024-06-03-21-37-25-251.png!*

 

*Please note:* if you remove the permission "FLEX_AUTHENTICATION" and ONLY the permission "SPIN_AUTHENTICATION" is assigned, then it works fine

!image-2024-06-03-21-39-11-150.png!
column366:
Standard Authentication window is displayed instead of the SPIN window if FLEX_AUTHENTICATION and SPIN_AUTHENTICATION are assigned

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2/PR | FTTH Wholebuy - Phase 2 | FTTH DGW/ DTAG telesales activation orders are failing after Tivano input due to "tae location/ home-id"
column41:
We have observed that FTTH DGW telesales activation orders are failing after Tivano input.

 

*Error :*

<CodeValue>406</CodeValue>
<Description>[HTTPAdaptor] Can not connect to HTTP Server[dsllte-api-pr.internal.vodafone.com:443], Status[406], Message[INVALID_INPUT_DATAinvalidorder/installation/desired-installation-dateNot a valid parameter for this address-product-combinationinvalidorder/installation/location-details/tae-locationNot a valid parameter for this address-product-combinationOrder data could not be validated]</Description>

 

*Test Data:*

Environment: ACC2/PR

Order ID: 1072783, 1072293

Barcode ID: VDE5602817464, VDE5602816728

 

*Steps to reproduce:*
 * Login to Omnius Telesales channel.
 * Perform serviceability with FTTH presales/redensification address.
 * Configure a FTTH DGW Product.
 * Proceed to checkout.
 * Submit order.
 * Track order in OGW.

 
*Expected Result:*
 Order should successfully submit to BE and for FTTH DGW and FTTH DTAG phase2 order 
 * tea location/ home-id should not be provided to Tivano

  
*Actual Result:*
 Orders are failing after Tivano input, because "tae location/ home-id" is provided to Tivano

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2/PR | New activation | FTTH Phase 2 | Getting wrong status in information tab after availability check for FTTH DGW & GPON address
column41:
While performing FTTH Wholebuy – Telekom & Deutsche Glasfaser Phase 2 scenario with E2E address we observed that getting wrong status in information tab after availability check for FTTH DGW address
 
*Steps to Reproduce:*
1) Login to Omnius with Telesales/Retail channel
2) Perform Serviceability at FTTH Phase DGW addresse
3) Check information tab after availability check
4) Observe status in availability check 

 

*Actual Result :*
In Wichtig (Important) tab
1) Bullet point indicatior color for below information is red
   Glasfaser Regio-Klasse
   Projekt-Referenz (Ausbaugebiet)
   Leitungslieferant
   Ausbau-Status

2)Produktverfügbarkeit (Product availability) tab
  Fibre bandwidths from VFP are shown in the horizontal bar 'GLASFASER' in Yellow and     Red color

3)Marketing-Nachricht(Marketing Message)
 This information shows information about FTTH GPON(GigaGemeine) 

*Expected Result:*
In Wichtig (Important) tab
1)Bullet point indicatior color for below information should Green
   Glasfaser Regio-Klasse
   Projekt-Referenz (Ausbaugebiet)
   Leitungslieferant
   Ausbau-Status
2)Produktverfügbarkeit (Product availability) tab
  Fibre bandwidths from VFP shoild be shown in the horizontal bar 'GLASFASER' in Yellow 
3)Marketing-Nachricht(Marketing Message)
 FTTH GPON(GigaGemeine) should not available 





  
Test Data:
Environment: ACC2/PR
*Address used:* 

Noorderloog 19, 26474 Spiekeroog

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | Getting "An error occurred while generating the document" when clicking on update BEW document.
column41:

Please find below request:

!image-2024-05-31-20-13-30-317.png|width=452,height=210!

{*}Test Data{*}:

Please refer below test data
|Stack|Test Data|
|Cabel|932232728|
|DSL|FN_001951027040|

Error Message:
{code:java}
<env:Fault xmlns:env="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/">
<faultcode>env:Server</faultcode>
<faultstring>
<WebServiceUALException><n:ROOT xmlns:n='http://amdocs/iam/api/GeneralResponse' xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'><Event/><Error><Number>JESIERR-3</Number><Description>[error: cvc-minLength-valid.1.1: string length (0) is less than minLength facet (1) for type of CustomerSequence element in VFDEPermissionDetailsType in namespace http://amdocs/vfde/permission/VFDESetPermissionsInput, error: cvc-minLength-valid.1.1: string length (0) is less than minLength facet (1) for type of CustomerSequence element in VFDEPermissionDetailsType in namespace http://amdocs/vfde/permission/VFDESetPermissionsInput]</Description></Error></n:ROOT></WebServiceUALException>
</faultstring>
<faultactor>VFDESetPermissionEG</faultactor>
<detail>
<ual:WebServiceUALException xmlns:ual="http://amdocs/vfde/permission/VFDESetPermission" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:type="xsd:string">
Code=JESIERR-3:Description=[error: cvc-minLength-valid.1.1: string length (0) is less than minLength facet (1) for type of CustomerSequence element in VFDEPermissionDetailsType in namespace http://amdocs/vfde/permission/VFDESetPermissionsInput, error: cvc-minLength-valid.1.1: string length (0) is less than minLength facet (1) for type of CustomerSequence element in VFDEPermissionDetailsType in namespace http://amdocs/vfde/permission/VFDESetPermissionsInput]
</ual:WebServiceUALException>
</detail>
</env:Fault>{code}
*Steps to Reproduce:*

      1. Login Omnius as a Retail Agent and select shop.
      2. Search existing Cable Private customer which is having BEW Version <System (less than system) and retrieve with Legacy search.
      3. Verify the yellow banner message to Retail Agent so that Agent will be aware that the current BEW status is not up-to-date.
        German Text- Bitte fehlende oder aktuellere Beratungseinwilligung vom Kunden in der Produktübersicht (meine Produkte) einholen.
        English Text - Please obtain missing or more up-to-date consulting consent from the customer in the product overview (my products) 
      4. Agent has clicked on "BEW bearbeiten" button to initiate the process to edit BEW permissions.
      5. Agent has selected "BEW erfassen" option and initiated the process to capture BEW details.
      6. BEW Voicelog page will be visible after click on Weiter button.
      7. Select the both ADV and DEV checkbox and click on document creation.
      8. Generate document data request will trigger(I1021_GenerateDocument) towards OGW to OM after click on Document creation.
          - Retrieve document request will trigger(I1016) 
       9. Click on Drucken button, the document will be downloaded.
      10.  Update BEW(BEW aktualisieren).

 
     {*}Actual Result{*}:  Getting "An error occurred while generating the document" when clicking on update BEW document.
      
    *Expected Result* : Should not get error while generating the document" when clicking on update BEW document.

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | OS-9063 | Banner message text for Postpaid Activation fees added again is not correct
column41:
Hello,
While performing D2COC scenario we observed Yellow message banner with text 'Der Anschlusspreis von 39.99€ wurde wieder hinzugefügt' is not visible

*We observed activation fee 39.99€ instead of 39,99€ here we expecting comma instead of dot as 39,99€*

Text in yellow banner should be 'Der Anschlusspreis von 39,99€ wurde wieder hinzugefügt'

*Test data*: GSM1721751999

*Pre-requisite*: Agent has permission DEBIT_TO_CREDIT permission

*Reference Story*: https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-47282

*Steps to reproduce*:

*Configurator*:
1. Login to Retail Channel.
2. Select mobile package
3. Select hardware & Tariff
4. Fill necessary details.
5. Do check the D2COC check box
6. Enter debit MSISDN and click on validation button
7. The First Name and Last Name fields (3 in total) should be auto-filled with data once the validation is successfully completed by the OGW response
8. The memo radio buttons should allow selecting only one option at a time (standard radio button feature).
9. Subscriber activation Fees should be added back to the mobile postpaid activation package, if the D2C with owner change checkbox is unchecked. Meaning, the scenario is now a normal Postpaid ACQ
10. Omnius should show the banner/message to the Agent “Activation Fee <9.99> EUR was added to the shopping cart…”

*Actual result*: Now in yellow banner message activation fee is *39.99€ instead of 39,99€*
"Der Anschlusspreis von 39.99€ wurde wieder hinzugefügt"

*Expected Result*: Omnius should show the banner/message text to the Agent should be

Yellow banner with message: *Der Anschlusspreis von 39,99€ wurde wieder hinzugefügt*

29/May/24 4:31 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Irina added a comment -
 
 
 
Hi [~pallavi.kokate1@vodafone.com]  ,
may I ask you to provide the complete I1006 logs?

According to the User Story
[!https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/story.svg!|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED2W90S-228][OS-46690] OMNIUS SAP-OIL: I want to receive EID number and SAPLocationType for e-sim compatible hardware Order/Package [OS-46690] - Vodafone Global Jira



We have a limit on the length of the SAPLocationType field. Lenght must not exceed 11 characters. If the length is greater, we shouldn`t submit this field to OGW.

Let`s consider the initial SAP file OSF_SAPSTAT_20240517104305.csv

!image-2024-05-29-16-29-33-254.png! The length of NOT_VFSTORE is 11. We have one more valueable CR character(in the green frame) - a carriage return. So this is the 12th.


We need to remove that extra carriage return, and the correct file will look like this:

!image-2024-05-29-16-30-23-451.png!

There is only one extra character left LF - line feed which is not valuable while parsing.

 

Considering all mentioned above we have several ways:
 # Remove this extra Carriage return symbol from the initial file - the most preferable way
OR

 # Extend the length up to 12 while parsing

 ;;;

column611: Code Fix
column916:
29/May/24 10:15 AM;arndt.vorrath@vodafone.com;Hello Ran, I guess this is exactly the problem we talked about two weeks ago:

In the property_env_ACC2.xml file, there is this line for the proxy configuration:  <PROXY_SOLSTICE>46.190.173.79:8080</PROXY_SOLSTICE>

However, there is also this remark in the property file:

 <!--If Proxy if required then populate as <PROXY_SOLSTICE>PROXY=47.73.108.134:8080;</PROXY_SOLSTICE>

So for my understanding, we have to change the configuration line to this: <PROXY_SOLSTICE>{color:#de350b}*PROXY=*{color}47.73.108.134:8080{color:#de350b}*;*{color}</PROXY_SOLSTICE>;;;

Shrikrushna Arjun Kaphare 
{color:#172b4d}added a comment -{color}
 
 If the agent has secondary roles assigned & those secondary roles have ALLOW_TELESALES/ ALLOW_RETAIL permission only then that button will be seen, as its related to role change if agent used for login has other roles assigned only then we can change to other roles.
 
Summary of CR724
!94648bad-105d-491e-9719-0c9aba79c8e3.png!
 
PFA
 
 
Note : 
that agent after logging in can move to other roles \{button Change Business function option will be visible} if & only if additional roles/ secondary roles are assigned to the agent used to login.. 
If no additional roles then button Change Business function option will not be visible - This is existing function, 
{ on release 9.18.14-B2 ST5 ( w8.2) - EXISTING} 

Only new change according to CR724:

Change Business function option will be visible if & only if additional roles/ secondary roles are assigned to the agent used to login & those additional roles/ secondary roles have permission ALLOW_TELESALES/ALLOW_RETAIL to be viewed in the respective channel Telesales or Retail. 

please check the agent used in ACC env for their additional roles is assigned & permissions of those additional roles
 
 ;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | OS-9063 | Banner message text for Postpaid Activation fees added again is not visible
column41:
Hello,
While performing D2COC scenario we observed Yellow message banner with text 'Der Anschlusspreis von 39.99€ wurde wieder hinzugefügt' is not visible

Text in yellow banner should be 'Der Anschlusspreis von 39,99€ wurde wieder hinzugefügt'

*Test data*: GSM1721751999

*Pre-requisite*: Agent has permission DEBIT_TO_CREDIT permission

*Reference Story*: https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-47282

*Steps to reproduce*:

*Configurator*:
1. Login to Retail Channel.
2. Select mobile package
3. Select hardware & Tariff
4. Fill necessary details.
5. Do check the D2COC check box
6. Enter debit MSISDN and click on validation button
7. The First Name and Last Name fields (3 in total) should be auto-filled with data once the validation is successfully completed by the OGW response
8. The memo radio buttons should  allow selecting only one option at a time (standard radio button feature).
9. Subscriber activation Fees should be added back to the mobile postpaid activation package, if the D2C with owner change checkbox is unchecked. Meaning, the scenario is now a normal Postpaid ACQ
10. Omnius should show the banner/message to the Agent “Activation Fee <9.99> EUR was added to the shopping cart…”

*Actual result*: Now in yellow banner message activation fee is 39.99€ instead of 39,99€
"Der Anschlusspreis von 39.99€ wurde wieder hinzugefügt"

*Expected Result*: Omnius should show the banner/message text to the Agent should be

*Yellow banner with message*: Der Anschlusspreis von 39,99€ wurde wieder hinzugefügt

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | OS-9063 | Omnius is not allows to process from new connection section after Authenticating customer with MTAN Authentication method due Invalid customer date of birth.
column41:
While performing D2COC scenario we observed Omnius is not allows to process from new connection section after Authenticating customer with MTAN Authentication method due Invalid customer date of birth.

*Test data*: GSM1721751999

*Pre-requisite*: Agent has permission DEBIT_TO_CREDIT permission

*Reference Story:* https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-44165

*Steps to reproduce*:

*Configurator*:
1. Login to Retail Channel.
2. Select mobile package
3. Select hardware & Tariff
4. Fill necessary details.
5. Do check the D2COC check box
6. Enter debit MSISDN and click on validation button
7. The First Name and Last Name fields (3 in total) should be auto-filled with data once the validation is successfully completed by the OGW response
8. The Date of Birth Field should be non-editable and should follow the DD.MM.YYYY format

*Actual result*: Omnius is not allows to process from new connection section after Authenticating customer with MTAN Authentication method due Invalid customer date of birth.

*Expected Result*: Omnius is should allows to process from new connection section after Authenticating customer with MTAN Authentication method.

Please find the IDD shared by VF based on which the development was done

!image-2024-05-24-12-16-29-662.png!

column920:
27/May/24 5:16 PM;andreas.knocke@vodafone.com;Hi Nasir, Divya,

sorry but that statement is misleading, you should not look at the Kias spec "KIAS_CSM_IN_CSM582_EAI_Interface_eaiDtcValid.docx" having C(8) as YYYYMMDD

*but* the Tibco "ADE_006991_EAI_IDD_PPM_528173_RMS176178_OSF_CR765_Change_of_Contract_Partner_while_doing_D2C_Change_v1.1.docx" and "Service_Specification_EAI_OSF-001_D2CEligCheck-001_CheckD2CEligibility_v0.2.docx" and both are having definition of 
|*Name*|*Data Type*|*Field Type*|*Description*|*Possible Values*|*Default Value*|
|{color:#ff8b00}*CheckD2CEligibilityResponse*{color}|SOAP Message|M|*Response element*| | |
| ** |ban|NumberMax(9)|O|Billing Account Number.
Ban to whom the subscriber belongs| | |
| ** |birthDate|{color:#57d9a3}XSD:Date{color}|O|Customer’s birth date| | |

and XSD:Date is the format YYYY-MM-DD. So this is the only format you can expect in Tibco response and shared thru.;;;

<configured>{*}ANALOG{*}</configured>

Instead of

<configured>analog</configured>

 

POSFE is designed that our expectation for oldaccess element value is like below,

 
 # “keiner or  ANALOG or digital”  if customerContactPoint element value is “BPA or OSF”

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2/PR | New activation | Missing availability check information for FTTH DTAG/DGW presales and redensification address
column41:
While performing FTTH Wholebuy – Telekom & Deutsche Glasfaser Phase 2 scenario with VFP DTAG mock address we observed that Missing availability check information for FTTH DTAG presales and redensification address 
 
*Steps to Reproduce:*
1) Login to Omnius with Telesales/Retail channel
2) Perform Serviceability at VFP mock FTTH DTAG presales and redensification addresses 
3) Check information tab after availability check
4) Observe status in availability check 
 
*Actual Result:* Missing availability check information for FTTH DTAG presales and redensification address
1) For Redensification Phase:
   a) Result bar displays the color Gray in the GLAS icon in case of Redensification phases 
     of FTTH DTAG and mouseover message in serviceability Bar is missing
2) For Presales Phase:
   a) Result bar displays the color Red in the GLAS icon in case of Redensification phases          of FTTH DTAG and mouseover message in serviceability Bar is missing
3) In availability information,Indicatior color is red
4) New bullet point titled as 'Geplanter Ausbautermin' is missing.
5) For redensification, Tab "Produktverfügbarkeit": Fibre bandwidths from VFP are shown
    in the horizontal bar 'GLASFASER' in Gray color
6) For redensification and Presales,'Ausbau Status' information is missing
7) For Presales, Tab "Produktverfügbarkeit": Fibre bandwidths from VFP are shown in the
    horizontal bar 'GLASFASER' in Red color
 
*Expected Result:*
 
1.Result bar displays the color Orange in the GLAS icon in case of Redensification phases
   of FTTH DTAG and a mouseover message in Serviceability Bar.
  Mouse over message-"Es sind noch Bautätigkeiten notwendig, um diese Adresse ans 
  Glasfasernetz anzuschließen. Für Bestandskunden muss ein Glasfaser-Neuauftrag   
  über „Paket hinzufügen“ erfasst werden."
2.Result bar displays the color Gray in the GLAS icon in case of Redensification phases of
   FTTH DTAG and a mouseover message in Serviceability Bar.
  Mouse over message-"Es sind noch Bautätigkeiten notwendig, um diese Adresse ans
  Glasfasernetz anzuschließen. Für Bestandskunden muss ein Glasfaser-Neuauftrag  
  über „Paket hinzufügen“ erfasst werden."
3.In availability information,Indicator color should be green
4.New bullet point should show and titled as 'Geplanter Ausbautermin' (planned end of
   rollout). Corresponding date should display. This field is placed in 
  the section 'Glasfaser Detailinformation' between the fields Ausbaustatus and
  Downstream/Upstream
5.Tab "Produktverfügbarkeit": Fibre bandwidths from VFP should show in the horizontal 
   bar 'GLASFASER' in yellow color
6.'Ausbau Status': 
 a. For Yellow-Grey Ref Serviceability,Ausbau status should displays as "Presales:       
     vvmOngoing, planned" for FTTH TELEKOM.
 b. Indicator color should green 
 c. For Orange Ref Serviceability, validate Ausbau status displays as "Redensification:
     homesPassed, homesPassedPlus" for FTTH Telekom. 
 d. Indicator color should green 
7.For Presales, Tab "Produktverfügbarkeit": Fibre bandwidths from VFP are shown in the
  horizontal bar 'GLASFASER' in yellow color
 
  
Test Data:
Environment: ACC2/PR
*Address used:* 
DTAG Redensification Phase 🡪 65760 Eschborn, Düsseldorfer Str. 107
DTAG Preslaes 🡪 65760 Eschborn, Düsseldorfer Str. 109 

DG Presales 🡪 65760 Eschborn, Düsseldorfer Str. 108

 DG Nachverdichtung 🡪 65760 Eschborn, Düsseldorfer Str. 106
