column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 KUD standalone products blocked in checkout after IBAN validation
column41:
Currently KUD TV products for Unitymedia as well as for VKD cannot be booked, as failing in checkout with error message after IBAN Validation.

Steps to reproduce for Telesales channel:

1) Enter unitymedia or VKD adress -> new customer
2) Add KUD product e.g. GigaTV Net, 1.{-}6. Monat 0,{-}€
3) move to checkout, fill in customer details > customer adress in Germany
4) reach to IBAN section, type in GERMAN IBAN e.g. DE20700500000003658888 (Any German IBAN can be taken!)
->IBAN validation is running and successfull
5) Select invoice adress as customer adress and do NOT select any different bank account holder
6) Klick on "weiter" and get error message

!image-2024-05-17-12-12-14-876.png|width=427,height=260!

_{color:#ff0000}Die ausgewählten kabel-unabhängigen Produkte (z.B. GigaTV App und Net) lassen seit dem 01.04.2018 eine Nutzung innerhalb der gesamten EU zu. Aber nach gesetzlichen Vorgaben nur von Kunden mit festem Wohnsitz in Deutschland.){color}_

_{color:#ff0000}Die Prüfung der Bankverbindung hat ergeben, dass eine ausländische Bankverbindung oder ein abweichender Kontoinhaber angegeben wurden.{color}_

_{color:#ff0000}Leider kann aus diesen Gründen die Prüfung auf festen Wohnsitz in Deutschland nur über den nächsten Vodafone-Shop erfolgen. Bringen Sie hierzu Ihren Personalausweis oder eine Meldebescheinigung mit.{color}_

 

We are not using foreign customer adress or foreign IBAN, and also +*not*+ using foreign invoice adress or different bank account holder
It is not the problem, that its going to be validated if there is any data from foreign countries used! The validation itself is correct process - but the result is wrong! It has to be identified by the system, that this customer is allowed to pay the products so we are able to move to the next section.

 

It seems the booking works sometimes, and sometimes not. Or maybe only for specific constellation of KUD products it works. We need to investigate if there is an issue with the software or not

This issue will be fixed after the merge for CR780/OAF-744 in ACC2 env

Please check possible side effects from CR780 Change of payment validation check for existing SEPA mandat which was one of the last production fixes and is available on both ACC

column1: OSF | Wave9.0 | ACC2 | Omnius allows to select new identification method in Kundenidentifikation section for second delivery use case.
column41:
While performing Second delivery flow in Telesales channel, We have observed, Omnius is allowing to select new identification method in checkout.

Response body:
{code:java}
{"error":false,"data":[{"Price":"\u20ac 0.00","Method":"Online","isDisabled":false},{"Price":"\u20ac 0.00","Method":"Door","isDisabled":false},{"Price":"\u20ac 0.00","Method":"Store","isDisabled":false},{"Price":"\u20ac 0.00","Method":"DHLFilialident","isDisabled":false}]}{code}
Please find below screenshots:

1. Agent clicks on SECOND DELIVERY (Zweitversand) button.

!image-2024-05-16-19-08-58-897.png|width=379,height=283!

2. Created a valid shopping cart with selection of Hardware in shopping cart.

!image-2024-05-16-19-10-07-792.png|width=387,height=203!

3. Customer identification section is in editable mode.

!image-2024-05-16-19-11-28-632.png|width=534,height=281!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Agent logged in Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Agent loaded existing Customer which is eligible for second delivery.
 # Agent clicks on SECOND DELIVERY (Zweitversand) button and created a valid shopping cart
 # Agent reached to checkout page on Customer data section.
 # Verify Customer identification section.

Actual: Omnius allows to select new identification menthod in Kundenidentifikation section for second delivery use case.

Expected: *Agent should see ident method section in read only mode as Agent cannot change manually* and Agent should see error banner with text message in case same Original order ident method is not available in interface RetrieveIdentificationMethods response and sales flow should stop.

Reference story: OAF-101 OMNIUS : CHCK As an Agent, i wanted to validate ident method for Second Delivery Order/package from Original order,so that Agent will process same ident method without any change. - Vodafone Global Jira

30/May/24 3:56 PM;pallavi.kokate1@vodafone.com;Yes Ari assigning back this Defect to OGW,same comment in PRT as well

• We found that it is working fine in case of Postpaid customers
• We checked OGW logs and found that EAI is sending simCardSize in GetSubscriber Response of Prepaid customers

column936:
31/May/24 7:37 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Feedback via Email

According Amdocs  KIAS behaves in following way:

SIM_SIZE field (introduced with CS1506) is populated only in MMC Market and it is populated from sim_size of main Sim Card for Subscriber

SIM_SIZE field does not exists in MMO Market

SIM_CARD_SIZE field (introduced in CS866) is populated in MMC Market with hard coded value in case that sim_size of main Sim Card is Duobill, Tricard/Twi Card. For all other main sim Types (eSim, Tripplesim) it is empty.

SIM_CARD_SIZE field is populated with sim_size of main Sim Card of subscriber in MMO Market

In EAI the fields are according Spec (is MFSubscriber-007:GetSubscriber used from OSF ?) mapped 1:1
|SIM_SIZE| |GetSubscriberResponse/subscriberDetails/additionalData/simSize|
|SIM__CARD__SIZE| |GetSubscriberResponse/subscriberDetails/simCardSize|

I propose to check in a common call to avoid both - KIAS and OGW - are doing things and in the end we will again have a mismatch [~gaurav.lanjewar1@vodafone.com]  [~alka.kshirsagar2@vodafone.com] ;;;

column917:
16/May/24 7:17 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;hi All, As discussed over the call --post analysis we found that for ACC2 environment current connections are as below 
Mobile -->OPT
DSL--> IT 

So where we trigger any DSL order-- customer creation is getting done in DSL IT Env but specific the SetPermission call configuration for EAI(OPT) is pointing to PR Env. so current problem is that SetPermission is trying to search a IT env created customer in PR due to which we are getting no customer found issue

In EAI connections are as below :-
EAI(OPT)-->PR
EAI(INT)-->IT

So this defect would need to be tested once we switch to PR env;;;

column1: OSF | Wave9.0 | ACC2 | Hardware unavailability error message not showing correctly in delivery section in case selected product not available in stock.
column41:
We have observed, Hardware unavailability error message not showing correctly in delivery section in case selected product not available in stock.

Please find below screenshot:

!image-2024-05-09-17-58-21-568.png|width=458,height=498!

error

message

productStockUnavailable
: 
true{code}
Steps to Reproduce:
1. Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
2. Select shop and Create Mobile Postpaid package with no available HW in Local stock.
3. Proceed to checkout.
4. Select Handout to store delivery option.
5. Omnius shows error message (Keine Direktherausgabe wegen Nicht-Verfügbarkeit möglich. Bitte wähle eine andere Lieferoption.).

Actual: Hardware unavailability error message not showing correctly in delivery section in case selected product not available in stock.

In case a product not available in stock is selected and agent selects the direct delivery method then agent can see below message
German: "Keine Direktherausgabe wegen Nicht-Verfügbarkeit möglich. Bitte wähle eine andere Lieferoption."
English: "No direct release possible due to non-availability. Please choose another delivery option."

Reference story: OTF-910 OMNIUS_CHECK_As an Agent, knowing about the hardware stock available I want to continue with the sales flow after selecting direct release delivery method in case the service ProductStockList fails due to technical error/Timeout. - Vodafone Global Jira

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | Solstice | PartyType = DC is not populated in the fulfilment logs on selecting delivery option as DHL Packstation
column41:
While performing below scenario :
Perform New activation of solstice order with alternative delivery addressDelivery to DHL Packstation
We have observed that <cbc:PartyType>*DC*<cbc:PartyType> is missing in the submit order fulfilment logs.
Order ID : 1062315

Steps to Reproduce :
1)Login to telesales channel
2)Select solstice package 
3)Select tariff
4)Select delivery option as "delivery to DHL packstation"
5)Submit the order
6)Go to fulfilment logs and check tag : <cbc:PartyType>*DC*<cbc:PartyType>

Expected Result : PartyType attribute value should be *DC* upon selecting delivery address as "delivery to DHL packstation"
Actual Result : PartyType = DC is missing in the logs

PFA logs and screenshots of steps.
column366: PartyType = DC  could not be validated for orders with delivery address to DHL packstation so customer might not get the delivery to the right adress
column611: based on the latest update of the corresponding user story, the current behaviour is accepted.

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | CR 724 | Agent with primary role having "Allow_Retail" permission is able to login to Telesales channel
column41:
We have observed that when agent is having its Primary role assigned *"Allow_retail"* permission and secondary role is assigned *"Allow_telesales"* permission then it goes to role change window, *but when we click on back button on the browser then it automatically logins to Telesales channel with primary role which is having "Allow_Retail" permission.*

 

*Steps to reproduce:*
 # Have multiple agent role in single user
 # Primary agent role should have "Allow_Retail" permission.
 # Secondary agent role should have "Allow_telesales" permission
 # Login to Telesales channel with user meeting above criteria
 # Since primary agent is having "Allow_Retail permission, role change window will be visible.
 # !image-2024-05-07-14-32-20-703.png|width=364,height=191!
 # Click on the back button of browser
 # !image-2024-05-07-14-32-56-370.png|width=361,height=188!
 # It will the login to Telesales channel with primary agent having "Allow_Retail" permission
 # !image-2024-05-07-14-34-28-441.png|width=363,height=191!
 # !image-2024-05-07-14-35-05-625.png|width=358,height=188!
 # In the above ss you can see we are logged into Telesales channel with Retail PA agent role, and we have assigned retail pa agent role "Allow_Retail" permission.

 

Expected result: If we click on back button we should be redirected to login page

Actual result: After clicking on back button we are able to login with retail permissions.

 

Note: We have tried clearing cache and cookies of browser, but still facing this issue.

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | CR724 | Getting role change window even when agent is having Telesales store view permission
column41:
We have observed that agent is getting *"Role Change Window"* when primary agent is having *"Telesales store view"* permission. This should not happen as primary agent is having *"Telesales store view"* permission, it should be able to login directly.

!image-2024-05-03-19-39-58-346.png|width=422,height=222!

 

*Use case:* 
 # Agent should have multiple agent role
 # Primary agent should have Only Telesales store view permission and no "Allow_Telesales" permission.
 # Secondary agent should have "Allow_telesales" permission.
 # observe the issue

*Steps to reproduce:*
 # Check primary agent is having Telesales store view permission
 # Verify primary agent is not having "Allow_telesales" permission
 # one of the secondary agent should have "Allow_Telesales" permission.
 # login to omnius in acc2
 # role change window is popping up.

 

*Expected result:* Role change window should not populate when primary agent is having                              Telesales store view permission.

 

*Actual Result:* Role change window is populating when primary agent is having                                          Telesales store view permission.
column366: CR724 functionality is not working as expected, so we are unable to test CR 724 due to this
column611: It is Working as Designed.
column915:
06/May/24 2:17 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Pragathi Prakash added a comment -
h3. [~akash.ubbu@vodafone.com] 
 
 
CR724 logic works in this way.
Agent has 3 levels of priority to login to Telesales/Retail
1. Agent Primary role 2.Agent Secondary role 3. Agent store view permission 

Case : Agent primary role has no ALLOW_TELESALES permission , Agent has Secondary roles with ALLOW_TELESALES permission, Agent also has Telesales store view permission.
 # System is going to first check if agent primary role has permission to login to Telesales ( ie. as ALLOW_TELESALES/ ALLOW_RETAIL).

 # If agent primary role does not have permission, system is going to look out for Agent secondary role ie ( Business functions) & if the secondary role has ALLOW_TELESALES/ ALLOW_RETAIL permission, then agent is provided with ROLE CHANGE drop down to choose a Role. 
Note: 
Roles with ALLOW_TELESALES will be displayed in role change drop down in Telesales.
Roles with ALLOW_RETAIL will be displayed in role change drop down in Retail.

 # If the agent has no primary role or secondary role with ALLOW_TELESALES/ ALLOW_RETAIL PERMISSION then priority is given to Agent store view permission.

Based on this logic the above defect is invalid.

https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OAF-692;;;
column916:
06/May/24 3:04 PM;akash.ubbu@vodafone.com;Hi [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] ,

But we are unable to login with agent role in which primary agent doesn't have "Allow_Telesales"/"Allow_Retail" permission in case of multiple agent role present in a user.

That agent role will not be visible in "Change Business Function" option, since it doesnt have "Allow_Telesales" permission.

Could you tell us how we can change into role which doesnt have "Allow_telesales"/"Allow_Retail" permission;;;
column917: 06/May/24 4:00 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;I am checking with TechM and will share the expecation here later, to have the full picture of the functionality;;;
column918:
06/May/24 4:44 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;I have now discussed with TechM. 

Akash you are right, any Telesales/COPS role without permission "Allow_Telesales" will not be usable anymore, if the user has other roles which have the permission

1) If you have ONLY one role, and this role is without permission ""Allow_Telesales" , but this role has Telesale store view, you can log in
2) If ANY of the roles of your user has the permission "Allow_Telesales", you can only log in with this role which has the permission and the other roles cannot be used anymore, even not when trying to change via "Geschäftsfunktion ändern". Telesales store view setting will be ignored

I have painted the picture in enclosed power point - was checked by Pragathi
I will also share with requestor, as not sure if this is expected. This would mean each role needs either "Allow Telesales" or "Allow Retail", not possible without this permission anymore as its not so likely that some user has one role only.

For testing we should maybe check the following:
-> One user +*with only one role*+ without "allow Telesales" Permission, Telesales store view is set -> *should be able to login*

 

*and the roles we need to use should ALL get Allow Telesales/ Allow Retail*;;;
column919:
06/May/24 5:21 PM;akash.ubbu@vodafone.com;Hi [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] ,

For below scenario we are able to login to telesales channel successfully without "Allow_Telesales" permission and only Telesales store view permission.

*For testing we should maybe check the following:*
*-> One user +with only one role+ without "allow Telesales" Permission, Telesales store view is set -> should be able to login.*;;;
column920: 06/May/24 5:23 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~akash.ubbu@vodafone.com]  thanks for the quick check. Then I think we can close this defect OS-55580 with working as designed and need to make sure we assign Allow Telesales and Allow Retail to all Roles which are in regular use from testing team ;;;
column921: 06/May/24 6:33 PM;akash.ubbu@vodafone.com;Yes, will close the defect and send the mail to user management team with list of agent roles which needs to be assigned "Allow_telesales" and "Allow_retail" Permission.;;;

column366: Compatibility message shown in configurator for existing Red+ customers when agent is changing existing Red+ Member tariff.
column611:
This is a data issue in the used stub file and not relevant for production.

Reason:
The old tariff option of the subscriber (REDPLDOS) received two further mandatory included SOCs in KIAD last year: GPRSDEF and LTEDEF. 
Especially the LTEDEF is important here since it is also mandatory included in the new tariff option GM1FMOS (FamilyCard) and it is the master SOC of another mandatory included slave SOC: VOLTE.

Rule 68 - Disallow SOCs with lower priority in KIAS SOC OnlyOne Plausi{*}) and the product removed from cart and we can see same missing on {*}Final allowed products skus{*}:["F_OSF002_0","F_OSF003_0","F_OSF004_0","F_OSF005_0","F_OSF007_0","KRFLATEUUS","K5GFREE","KNO5GSA","KDASROW1D","KVF_DASRP","KVOWIFREEC","KSO_EL_SIM","KCFD_SMS","KLTEDEF"].

Based on above analysis this is purely the PCAT rules based on that we are getting the pop which says *"The following product(s): [KVOLTE] VoLTE Basic cannot be added because they are incompatible with the current selection"*
Open image-20240611-044647.png 
!e1378327-65f9-4762-9c08-a8dea97f032e.png!

column939: 11/Jun/24 1:07 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~thomas.wermke@vodafone.com]  please check last comment from TechM;;;
column940:
12/Jun/24 9:30 PM;thomas.wermke@vodafone.com;This is a data issue in the used stub file and not relevant for production.

Reason:
The old tariff option of the subscriber (REDPLDOS) received two further mandatory included SOCs in KIAD last year: GPRSDEF and LTEDEF. 
Especially the LTEDEF is important here since it is also mandatory included in the new tariff option GM1FMOS (FamilyCard) and it is the master SOC of another mandatory included slave SOC: VOLTE.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | CR 724 | Getting error while login with agent role not having Allow_Telesale or Allow Retail permission
column41:
We are getting below error while logging into Telesales or Retail channel when agent is not having "ALLOW_TELESALES" or "ALLOW_RETAIL" permission.

!image-2024-04-26-12-41-48-512.png|width=310,height=163!!image-2024-04-26-12-42-25-440.png|width=308,height=162!

 

Error: There is currently no shop assigned to you. Please contact the Sales Service Line

 

Normally even if agent does not have "Allow_Telesales" or "Allow_Retail" permission, then it should check for store view permission and even store view permission is not there then it should throw an error. But the error should be different not above error.

But in our case it does not have "Allow_Telesales" permission, but it has Telesales store view permission so it should be able to login without any error. But we are getting above error while logging in.

 

Steps to reproduce:
 # Check if agent role is not having "Allow_Telesales" permission
 # Check if telesales store view permission is assigned.
 # login to omnius
 # try to login
 # observe the error.

 

Expected result: Agent should be able to login successfully

Actual Result: Agent is getting error while login.
column366:
Without having "Allow_Telesales" role, Agent is not able to login although Store view setting is correct. Agents without the new permission are blocked.
Same to be checked with Retail permission.

Means: CR 724 functionality is not working as expected, so we are unable to test CR 724 due to this

column1: OSF | ACc1 ACC2 ACC3 | Wave 8.2.2 | Regression | Customer Identification Options are not getting enabled based on the HW Price Range
column41:
Performing New Activation Mobile we observed that Customer Identifications options are not getting enabled within mentioned range.

 

In Omnius, calculate the Ident method visibility based on total HW price in Order

e.g.
|*Total HW Price Range*|*Possible ident*|
|0-1000 €|All Ident possible|
|1000-1200 €|Only Store & Web Ident; (Hide/Disable?) Door Ident|
|greater than 1200 €|Only Web ident|

 

From <https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OAF-313>

 

With a  (mobile) shopping cart value smaller than 1.199 EUR the following ident methods are available in checkout:
 * Min 0€ / Max 1.199€
 * Online-Ident
 * Store-Ident
 * Door-Ident

With value higher 1.199 EUR
 * Online-Ident
 * Store Ident

 

 

Steps Reproduce:

1) Login to Telesales using BO agent

2) Configure the package and select HW with 0-1000 euros and check if we get mentioned or define all 4 customer identification options during checkout in customer identification section

 

Actual Result

Currently if we select any HW within Defined range we see unexpected behavior during checkout in Customer identification section and its not working as expected following below table rules
|*Total HW Price Range*|*Possible ident*|
|0-1000 €|All Ident possible|
|1000-1200 €|Only Store & Web Ident; (Hide/Disable?) Door Ident|
|greater than 1200 €|Only Web ident|

 

Expected Result:

HW selected from Configurator should show the number of options in customer identification section accordingly following the below table
|*Total HW Price Range*|*Possible ident*|
|0-1000 €|All Ident possible|
|1000-1200 €|Only Store & Web Ident; (Hide/Disable?) Door Ident|
|greater than 1200 €|Only Web ident|
column366: HW selected within mentioned range does not show the respective customer identification option in section

column921:
24/Apr/24 12:48 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Instructions to switch off CR 553 .
 
(1) Stop the ProcessSOS_kafka eg

ProcessSOS_kafka.egxml will be present under ogwf/properties/eg/vfde/ProcessSOS_kafka.egxml
or in jesi in OGWF under events tab under vfde folder

 
or in some builds ProcessSOS_kafka.egxml might be under ogeg/properties/eg/vfde/ProcessSOS_kafka.egxml
or in jesi in OGEG under events tab under vfde folder
 

(2) Stop JMS_AUXILIARY_KAFKA_STATUS_EG eg
 
JMS_AUXILIARY_KAFKA_STATUS_EG.egxml will be present under ogwf/properties/eg/vfde/JMS_AUXILIARY_KAFKA_STATUS_EG.egxml
or in jesi in OGWF under events tab under vfde folder

3)  Start the ProcessSOS eg
 
ProcessSOS.egxml will be present under ogwf/properties/eg/vfde/ProcessSOS.egxml
or in jesi in OGWF under events tab under vfde folder.
 

Note: Also Build created after 18th April 2024 on WAVE 9 will have CR 553 by default turned off.;;;

and follow below point 


The Visibility of Geschäftsfunktion ändern tab depends on the agent secondary role & its assigned Store view permission ALLOW_TELESALES or ALLOW_RETAIL

Example:
 # Agent1 has Primary role SUPERAGENT with ALLOW_TELESALES & ALLOW_RETAIL Permission is assigned.

 # Agent1 also has few Secondary roles assigned ie TELESALES, BACKOFFICE, COPS AGENT.

 # 
 ## If Secondary roles does not have ALLOW_TELESALES permission Geschäftsfunktion ändern tab will not be visible in TELESALES channel as we only allow to change the agent role for secondary agents roles with ALLOW_TELESALES. (Same logic for Retail )

 # 
 ## If Secondary roles have ALLOW_TELESALES permission Geschäftsfunktion ändern tab will be visible in TELESALES channel as we only allow to change the agent role for secondary agents roles with ALLOW_TELESALES. (Same logic for Retail )
_*Note :*_ Geschäftsfunktion ändern tab & drop down will show only Secondary agent roles list with respective store view permission ALLLOW_TELESALES or ALLOW_RETAIL.

 # Unless & until Secondary roles for the agent does not have the respective store view permission then change of role ( Geschäftsfunktion ändern tab ) is not visible.;;;

column1: NEW CR OSF | ACC1 | Wave 8.2 | sliding prices are not interpreted as expected
column41:
{color:#ff0000}The priority is set to "Blocker" as the issue is a show stopper for the Go Live of : [https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PORPDT-79] 
Without a fix the feature can not be deployed into production.{color}

 

Test data:

Browser: Chrome
Environment: ACC1 
Channel: Telesales + Retail

Steps to reproduce the issue:
 - Enter address: Goethestr. 27 26409 Wittmund Wittmund
 - Select package: "Kabel Internet & Phone"
 - Select tariff: "[3BV:B09] GigaZuhause 250 Kabel, 1.-9. Monat 19,99 €"
 - Select goody on "Gutschriften und Aktionen" section: "[JL5] Gutschrift GigaZuhause Young: 1.-9. Monat: 0 €, 10.-24. Monat: -5 €, danach 0 €"
 - open basket

The prices are not calculated as expected.
As a consequence of the wrong basket also the contract summary is incorrect.

!image-2024-04-10-18-00-56-136.png|width=856,height=463!  

+Pre-Analyses of product configuration team:+
OSF uses the 'Price sliding' field from the Product Catalog to configure the way the price periods are shown in the frontend:

!screenshot-1.png|width=338,height=226!

The numbers in this field are however interpreted as absolute points in time. They should however be interpreted as relative time intervals.

+Concretely this means:+

Price sliding '9:6:' should be interpreted as 0.-9. month, 10.-15. month, 16. month onward.
Currently it is interpreted as 0.-9. month, 0.-6. month, whatever comes afterward.
This obviously does not make any sense, since the second period ends before the first one, so the consequence in the frontend is, that the second period is ignored.

+The obvious fix therefore is:+
The numbers in the "Price sliding" field should always be interpreted as *relative time* intervalls.

 

+Additional proof:+
When checking in the OSF Backoffice for the product properties, the price_sliding of JL5 looks like this:

!image-2024-04-09-15-34-39-869.png!

Looking at this in overview in the frontend, the second time intervall seems to be ignored:

!image-2024-04-10-18-00-56-136.png|width=423,height=229!

Manually changing it to 15 then leads to the following view in OSF:

column1: SPN-OPT-000141765-O Z_INC02743011A || INC000088419954 OSF | Wave 8.2 | ACC1, ACC2 and ACC3 | CS/CD is taking time to generate in OM
column41:
We have observed that OM is taking too long to respond which is leading to delay of generation of CS-CD. It is taking almost 30 mins to respond.

!image-2024-03-26-13-28-55-505.png!

 

 

In above image OM recieved the request at 8:06:43 and OM responded at 8:36:36, so its almost taking 30 mins to respond.

 

Steps to reproduce:
 # Place any Stack order
 # go to CS -CD page
 # observe the issue

 

Expected result: CS-CD should be generated within a minute

Actual result: CS-CD is generating after 30 mins, due to OM responding late.

column956:
15/May/24 9:53 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,

yes, currently the fix is almost ready after discussions with design team and Ketaki.

in this fix the 24 retry will not be in use anymore, instead the retry will be determined by the ogw_error_handler table.

it will decide how many times to retry, and how much time to wait between the calls.

for this flow the retry will be active for empty response from oneDMS or OGWERR-9900 error code return

for example:
this is a record from the table:

{
    "ERROR_CODE":"OGWERR-9900",
    "ERROR_CATEGORY":"Technical",
    "IGNORE_ERROR_IND":"N",
    "RETRYABLE_IND":"TRUE",
    "MAX_RETRY_TIMES":"3",
    "RETRY_WAIT_TIME":"10",
    "MAX_WAIT_TIME":null,
    "STATUS_TO_SET":null,
    "CHANNEL":"TELESALES",
    "SERVICE_CALL":"ASYNC",
    "SERVICE_NAME":"OneDMS"
}
so the flow will retry 3 times and the wait time will be 10 seconds between every try.;;;

column941:
18/Apr/24 12:36 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;There was a meeting between Kshitij and Andreas with following outcome:
 * Values like "AccountCategory" in Omnius are derived from OGW: Here:- _AccountCategory_ in getCustomerResult for index search and _Region_ in retrieveCustomerInfo mode1 for LegacySearch.
 * As the ADDRESS REGION is in UM Area - it is treated as UM customer, even though he belongs to the VKD Stack

h4. _Possible SD option to be validated/proven:_ 
 * Derive customer stack from GlobalID prefix ("legacy stack")  instead of address region
 * IF improvements required as this is only known by OGW (Omnius can only see LK_ from linked customers) - e.g. introducing new attribute to indicate customers product stack:
 * CustomerSearch()
 * getCustomerDetails()
 * [@Mitra, Gaurab, External Vendor|mailto:gaurab.mitra@amdocs.com]: We should investigate if further interfaces have to be considered (To be discussed on next CR meeting)

[@Kshitij.Srivastava@comviva.com|mailto:kshitij.srivastava@comviva.com]: To check UseCases in Omnius to be considered for an improvement

Further benefit: Omnius Performance increase If product stack information is directly provided by OGW 

 

So team is working on possible solution but will take some time ;;;

24/Jan/24 3:56 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  I was not creating any order, I am just scanning portal UI tool from time to time to find unidentified issues. And within this quality check I have found tickets with this error message. 

 

After some analysis I have identified, that it seems to be this scenario:

-> Search existing unitymedia customer and perform Move to VKD adress 

 

this is example Order ID from ACC1 - it failed with 2 sky tickets

One ticket because of invalid VPKN (issue is solved, please ignore that) and second sky ticket was for setpermission.


Unfortunately Sky ticket were cleared in between so I am not able to find my two tickets anymore..... But hopefully you can reproduce on your environment for a Move from Unity to VKD.

Seems like in this case the existing customer ID from unity is taken over, instead of recognizing that customer will get a new customer ID from VKD for Move scenario

 

Order ID 782545, Customer ID 1009755201 (initial customer before Move) 

!image-2024-01-24-11-21-17-927.png!

 

Same seems to happen when moving from Unity Cable to DSL product. 

So please check flow Unity Cable to VKD Cable Move, and Unity Cable to DSL Move

 ;;;

Hi [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com]  ,

Further based on investigation above is the expected behavior. Which means for the existing customer we are getting the region value from Install Base and if region value which is from the IB or from the serviceability(in ACQ) is not matching with the below table data which is agreed during the design, then OSE send empty <CustomerList><CustomerDetails>{*}<TargetSystem>{*}.

If for any new region value VF expects to send *TargetSystem* value then it has to be added to OSE via SRT

!image-2024-01-30-16-58-09-079.png!;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 8.2 & Wave 8.2.1 | ACC1 ACC3 |  Map is not available in delivery section When delivery option as delivery to Packing station
column41:
Map is not available in delivery section When delivery option as delivery to Packing station

Steps to Recreate:

Env ACC1

Place an order in ACC1

Select the delivery option as Delivery to Parcel shop or Packing Station

Check whether the map is available

 

Actual Result :Map is not available

Expected Result:Map should be available to select the pack station
column366: Delivery option: Delivery to pack station can only be selected via list and not via map
column611:
The Maps JavaScript API team regularly updates the API with new features, bug fixes, and performance improvements. 

As part of this activity some older version of the Maps JavaScript API version are deprecated. Currently its corrected by using version which is available.

Issue might reoccur if Maps JavaScript API deprecate the currently used version 

Solution: New keys have been supplied to T5D for the Map issue with different functionalities per Env. Now the Map is getting displayed for all ACC envs

column1: OSF | Wave 8.1.5 | ACC2 | Mobile retail Sky Tickets is not visible in SKY tool for ACC2
column41:
While performing below scenario,
|Perform Mobile Retail with invalid SIM/BAN and check if Sky ticket is generated and failed the sky ticket to check the status in order manager |

we observed that SKY ticket is generated in OGW but its not visible in SKY Tool .

!image-2024-01-15-18-38-53-787.png|width=389,height=219!

Steps to Reproduce:

Login to Retail in ACC2
Add Mobile postpaid package
Go to checkout
Fill details
Submit Order
OGW will create SKY Ticket
Check SKY ticket in SKY tool.

*Actual Result :* SKY ticket is not visible in SKY tool.

*Expected Result :* SKY ticket should be visible .

*Omnius order id:* 1034117, 1034227
column366: Agent cannot complete customer authentication as SKY Ticket is not visible in sky tool for "Mobile Retail with invalid SIM/BAN", therefore Order cannot proceed further.
column611: Fixed as merge in CN_18343 for ACC2 because production fix Z_PRT00135827A was rolled back

column41:
We tried placing an order with NE3 Address where Self install is no (ACC1)

in Access details we are getting the below error

({*}Your technical connection selection does not match){*}

!image-2023-12-15-18-50-55-105.png|width=406,height=222!

 

 

Steps to Recreate:

1)Take an address with NE3 and Self install=no(Example:51063,Köln ,Von-Galen-Str. 63) in unitymedia region

2)Select any of  the KIP Product(TV Will get added automatically)

3)checkout and move forward

4)check whether any error message is shown in Access Details

 

Actual: Error message is shown at access details page

Expected: No error message should be shown in Access details page 

Note:If we change the access details option to technician required for TV product then we are able to move forward without any issue

column41:

*Steps to reproduce:*

Login to Omnius Telesales channel

Select DSL Product

Proceed to checkout

Submit order

Track order in OGW

 

Expected Result:

Order should submit to BE 

 

Actual Result:

CONFIRMATION_OK OnOrderStatusChange Request not received from TIVANO.

Test Data:

Environment : PR /ACC2

Order id : 1024325  Barcode :  VDE5602747555

Order id : 104329   Barcode : VDE5602747559

Order id : 1024307 Barcode: VDE5602747528

Order id : 1024317 Barcode: VDE5602747545

column1: ON-HOLD | OSF Wave 8.1 | ACC2 |Existing customer scenario with GigaKombi does not work
column41:
Testenvironement: Test1b/ACC2

Testrun: Code Freeze regression testing OSF for PCAT Cable

Description: An existing customer cannot do anything with gigakombimarkers like VB4/VB5/VA1.
Always an errormessage appears in the extended shopping cart (see screenshot) and no further step is possible

Failed testcases:
[https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/SYSSHARQS-1699]

Small description of Teststeps:
Testcustomer: *934829320* (has an old TV product CGT1WG1)
Open OSF ACC2 Telesales
Load Testcustomer
Add a mobile tariff like *[KGM1LH30] GigaMobil L mit PremiumSmartphoneSpecial (Sub 30)*
With hardware "{*}[S00302349] Oppo Find X3 Pro Navy Blue - M{*}"
Go to the existing products of the customer
and click on Paket ändern
TV is opened
Select VB4 as gigakombi - marker
In small shopping cart gigakombi marker appears correctly
in extended shopping cart gigakombi marker appears but error message is thrown (see screenshot)

On ACC1/test3b the same test works correctly
column611: Logic for Gigakombi was changed & there is no GigaKombi available for TV. The markers VB4 + VB5 are not booked anymore. Also for KIP there wsa a change. VA1 was replaced with GKF and GKF is not booked for existing customers. Therefore the defect is not reproducible anymore
column910: As a workaround the agent can trigger execution of the posting rules by selecting and deselecting any product.
column915:
21/Nov/23 6:51 PM;johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com;Analysis results:

To prevent more issues related to [[OTF-902] KIPOPENEDMARKER not being sent in submit order xml || ADD and Drop Cable backend error - Vodafone Global Jira|https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OTF-902] we improved the detection of empty packages in OSF to prevent the agent from entering the checkout with such.

In this case however the package is not empty as it contains VB4. As such our rule should not trigger if the posting rules were executed correctly after clicking the button to create the GigaKombi bundle.

This issue must be fixed by OSF - the posting must be executed after the bundle is created and a product (like VB4) is added to the package.;;;

13/Dec/23 4:42 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;As explained in the call (and in previous comments on this ticket):
 * the checkout is blocked by a rule that comes from the pcat because the product OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER is not selected.
 * the product is added by the posting rules of the cable rules artifact if there is _any_ change to the TV package
 * after the bundle is created the TV package _is changed as it now contains VB4_
 * as checked in the logs: the posting rules are not called by OSF after the bundle is created

*OSF has to call the posting rules after any change to a cable package, otherwise inconsistencies regarding products/orders/etc are to be expected.* ;;;

Hari Shankar Malviya 
added a comment -
 
Hi Alexander/Simon,
 
 For extended shopping cart min max equal warning rules, there is not relation with cable post rule results or execution.
The rule which is problematic, is a max(0) rule and service to category rule. So if this rule’s service source expression evaluates to true than it will check if cart have max 0 number of products only from the target category. So if product OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER is not part of the package then problematic rule service source expression will evaluate to true and further it will show warning if from target category we have more then 0 products in cart.;;;

14/Dec/23 4:54 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;[~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com], I am not sure if there was any more specific documentation (I will keep searching for a bit), but the following HLD already has a section:
|*Cable artifact rules*
 
The Cable Catalog and PLM colleagues have requested their own rules engine to be applied in the configurator. This is realised with a plugin development where Cable colleagues can upload their Rules Artifact as part of the PLM process. This Rules Artifact consists of the same Sales Rules (in PHP language/cable-speak) that is used currently in ECC front-ends. OMNIUS will share the full-shoppingcart (all packages) to the Rules Artifact, the rules artifact will process ruling, and return the shoppingcart object with modified cable orderlines in Kabel TV, KIP and KUD packages to be displayed in OMNIUS. The Rules Artifact will be called both before a product is selected (on show of configurator, pre-condition) {*}as well as after selecting a product (on adding to the shoppingcart, post-condition){*}. OMNIUS will not be able to have special GUI handling like for internal OMNIUS sales rules when using the Artifact.|

Highlighting added by me.

Full document: [https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/sites/C3-B2B-OneSalesFoundation/IMPLEMENTATION%20Drop1/Deliverables/01%20V-HLD%20Vertical%20HLDs/HLD%202.0/V-HLD_01_Workpackage%201_Scenario%201c-v2%2018.docx]

 

From a slightly newer HLD:
|Apart from the Omnius compatibility rules for cable, specific precondition and postcondition rules from cable are also evaluated within the Cable Rules Artifact. *With each change in the configurator (for cable products) the Omnius rules and Cable rules artifact are evaluated in a loop, until a stable state is reached.* |

Full document: [https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/sites/C3-B2B-OneSalesFoundation/IMPLEMENTATION%20Drop1/Deliverables/02%20FA/FA-01%20Product%20Catalogue/FA-01_30%20HLD%20Wave%203_Product%20Catalogue-v2.11.docx]

column1: OSF Wave 8.1 ACC2 - ON HOLD OSIP-1359 Contract Summary: Price of old TV Product is missing (only OSF)
column41:
test environment: test1b /ACC2 Wave 8.1

Scenario: 
Existing Unitymedia cable customer with following inventory: legacy KIP Product (not Broadvision) and legacy TV Product (Code UMDKLM) orders GigaZuhause 1000 (Broadvision product) - Telesales 

Rabatt UMDTZBK is added --> this is correct / legacy TV product itself stays with "Digitaler Kabelanschluss m. Service)

Fill in all mandatory information in checkout section and move until Contract Summary creation

Contract Summary OSF:
{color:#de350b}Price "Digitaler Kabelanschluss m. Service" 0 Euro --> not ok, Price should be 20,99 Euro{color}

column366: Customer is getting wrong price on the contract summary in case of specific TV product constellations -> new change required
column611: No Change Required.
column915:
09/Nov/23 7:56 PM;johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com;From what I can see in VkdGateway the price of the product is correctly returned as:

"nonStandardRate": 17.64, 

which with VAT makes ~20.99€.

The product itself however does not seem to indicate that it has a price nor a non standard rate, both of which should however not be necessary for unity inventory products.

It is noteworthy that the product itself has no price configured in the product setup, maybe the display in the contract summary of OSF does not work if it is an inventory product without a price (and without a non standard rate actually configured in the product setup)?

To me this sounds a) like an OSF issue and b) not like a BV issue.;;;

column1: OSF | ACC3 | ON HOLD Wave 8.1 | IMPROVEMENT CR to fix DSL Telesales orders are getting stuck at OnHold-PendingDSLShop
column41:
While performing today sanity we observed that DSL telesales orders are stuck at state OnHold-PendingDSLShop. so that orders are not getting submitted to backend. {color:#de350b}*This is only for ACC3*{color}

*Steps to reproduce:*

Login to Omnius Telesales channel

Select DSL Product

Proceed to checkout

Submit order

Track order in OGW

 

*Expected Result:*

Order confirmation by DSL shop should came from Tivano/Eshop

Order should submit to BE 

 

Test data : 
Order id :  428201  , Barcode : VDE5600000076

Order id : 428193  , Barcode: VDE5600000058
column366: DSL Orders are not getting submitted to backend in case we are changing the sequence on OGW side for OGW order ID
column611: delivery of CR804
column915:
25/Oct/23 12:14 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;Defect to be kept ON-HOLD-- currently here the issue is that OGW is creating a BARCODE which can accept max 8 digits where the new sequence id which is changed for OGW order is is having 9 digits due to which when OGW is trying to search customer is CDM it counts the 8 digits starting from RHS where the last digit is ignored 
So in this case the new order id = 900000073 where while searching it is only calculating 73 ignoring all the 0 digits as they are null.
The last 9 digit =9 is been not counted at all as it only does counting until 8 digits which is 00000073 

To adapt these changes --we need to have a CR in OGW to implement the changes;;;

column919:
27/Sep/23 5:11 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I tested this on one of our cloud sandboxes with v9.17.0-BB123 and cable PCAT V2301_2023_10_00_020 with the mock [Cable_Address_Availability_KIP500_SI.|https://ash-sb5-telesales.osf.paps-vf.de/agent/account/login?showProductCodes=true&TC_ID=Cable_Address_Availability_KIP500_SI]

Result: during the checkout I can select 1V1 as a TV technician and TECYESKIP as a KIP technician.
The logs indicate that 1V1 is never passed to cable product logic as selected.
I attached the log of the session.
[^cable_rules_artifact_OS44322.log]

The log should contain an entry like "1V1|true" which it does not.

I also reproduced the issue with the mock [Cable_Address_Type_NE4-VVO|https://ash-sb5-telesales.osf.paps-vf.de/agent/account/login?showProductCodes=true&TC_ID=Cable_Address_Type_NE4-VVO] which results in VP0 being selectable in the checkout. Again in the log we cannot find VP0 ever being passed to the cable product logic as selected.

[^cable_rules_artifact_OS44322_VP0.log]

At this point I think this is a OSF bug, since cable logic cannot control when and with which products it is called by OSF.;;;
column921:
29/Sep/23 3:00 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;Hi Vikash,
as the logs show the PCAT returns VP0 and 1V1 as visible in this case, so maybe we have a different understanding what "visible" in this case means?
My understanding of visible in this case is:
 * the last call of the cable rules plugin by osf returns a list of packages, each containing a list of products.
 * a product is "visible" for a dropdown if the property "visible" in the last return value of the cable rules plugin for this particular product was "true".

 ** this is especially distinct from the "visibility" of tariffs in the configurator which depends on more information like:
 *** is the product selected
 *** is it configured to be shown in the configurator
 *** is the product "visible" according to the last result of the cable rules plugin

*According to the logs 1V1/VP0 is visible in this case but is never selected by OSF even if the agent selects it in the dropdown*

This is even underlined by the fact that 1V1/VP0 are shown in the dropdown {*}which would not be the case if the were not "visible"{*}.;;;

column932:
11/Oct/23 2:53 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;Hi Vikash,

I do not think it is related to CR676 as it has nothing to do with the json schema, but a change in that CR could of course have impacted OSE to behave differently. According to my knowledge however CR676 only had OGW impact until recently and should have no impact whatsoever on OSE and with which products OSE calls the cable product logic.

As I said before, from our perspective there is absolutely nothing cable can do about this *because we do not control with which products cable product logic is called by from OSE.*

*Please investigate in OSE why the cable product logic is not called with the product after it is selected in the checkout.* Before this is done there will be nothing we can do to help with this issue, so please refrain to assigning it back to me before this is investigated. If you have further question please set up a meeting with me.

Best regards

Simon;;;

column944:
06/Dec/23 8:20 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I further analysed this issue and found the following:

Orders created by OSF contain a field 
{code:json}
"apartmentDetails":{"technicianNeeded":
true/false
}
{code}
As far as I can tell from tests the field is always true if and only if the agent selected the technician_yes option in either the TV or the KIP dropdown during the checkout.

This information should also be passed to the cable rules plugin, in the field `IServiceAddress::technicianNeeded`.

After the selection of technician options in the dropdown the cable posting rules are executed again by OSF, but the the `technicianNeeded` field is not set to true (as it should be if the agent previously selected VP0/TECYESKIP in the technician dropdowns).

This can be checked by searching for `technicianNeeded` in the following log: [^cable_rules_artifact_OS44322_technicianNeeded.log] 
Notice that the last execution contains `TECYESKIP|true`, since the agent selected the kip technician to be necessary.

For fixing this bug the cable rules artifact logs can be used to check if the technician needed flag is passed to the cable rules plugin correctly.
In the meantime we will try to provide a workaround that might resolve most of the issues as well. We have an experimental workaround since version V2330_2024_01_00_032.
Until this issue is fixed on OSF side and we can remove our workaround again I would keep this ticket open however.;;;

column955:
10/Jan/24 9:28 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;[~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] 

Okay, let me go through your message step by step.

For the first test case:
 * I can reproduce it :)
 * I think that only the TV dropdown is shown is correct (according to the up to now still best documentation we have: [Scenario dimension "Technician appointment" - OSF - Vodafone Global Confluence|https://confluence.sp.vodafone.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=103985437]).
 * I think VP0 being selectable is also correct (again according to above documentation, and to some tests we have [Quelle von vkdTechnicianOptions.feature - productSetup - webgit (kabeldeutschland.de)|https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/FE/repos/productsetup/browse/4DevelopmentOnly/tests/unified/features/availability/vkdTechnicianOptions.feature#216-236]).
 * VP0 disappearing afterwards sounds problematic and without investigating I have no idea why it would.
 ** VP0 not being selected anymore however explains that my workaround doesn't work because it relied on the presence of the technician options instead of the flag.

For the second case:
 * I can reproduce the behaviour :)
 * I don't understand the problem with this though? For this particular example you can proceed either with no technician at all (TECNOKIP, TECNOTV are both selectable) or with a technician (TECYESKIP, 1V1 can be selected together).
 * If the issue is the error message, what would be the expected behaviour if a different technician selection would be made by the agent?
 * If the issue is that the TV dropdown is visible at all: that confuses me a bit as well, since our tests would indicate that only the kip options should be shown in this case: [Quelle von vkdTechnicianOptions.feature - productSetup - webgit (kabeldeutschland.de)|https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/FE/repos/productsetup/browse/4DevelopmentOnly/tests/unified/features/availability/vkdTechnicianOptions.feature#239-259]

column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (test2b) 

Channel: Retail + Telesales

Test address: Ottobrunner Str. 55 81737 München (NE4-VVO)

 

{color:#172b4d}*Please note:*{color}
 * {color:#172b4d}first we thought the Sky Error is related to KIP only, but if we create an order with KIP only on the same address, there is no Sky Error, e. g.: OSF Order ID: 999881{color}
 * {color:#172b4d}on NE3 addresses the bug does not appear:{color}

{color:#172b4d}!image-2023-09-22-13-58-49-056.png!{color}
 * {color:#172b4d}on ACC1 the bug does also appear:{color}

{color:#172b4d}!image-2023-09-22-13-39-25-797.png!{color}

 

 

{+}Actual result{+}: KIP Technician field for orders with TV and KIP is missing on NE4-VVO addresses

 

+Expected result:+ KIP Technician field for orders with TV and KIP should be displayed

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * load an ENV address, e. g.: Ottobrunner Str. 55 81737 München
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel TV"
 * select a TV tariff, e. g.: "[CKH8] Vodafone TV Cable"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"
 * select a TV tariff, e. g.: "[01H:B06] GigaZuhause 1000 Kabel, 1.-6. Monat 19,99 €"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * enter the customer data and click on the button "Weiter"

 

– > the field "Anschluss (WE) is bereits sehbereit / aktiv" is missing 

 

!image-2023-09-22-12-01-00-237.png!
column366: No business impact, but missing information for the Agent (Technician field in checkout is missing for the KIP part in case of orders with TV and KIP and in case of NE4-VVO addresses)

column915:
27/Sep/23 2:24 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I am not aware of any interface that lets cable control the display of whole dropdown sections. The answer why the whole section is missing can only be given by OSF.

If I had to guess I would assume OSF is hardcoded to check for TECYESKIP, TECNOKIP, UMTECKIP:NOO, UMTECKIP:YES. One of the relevant tests in our test suite is likely:
{code:java}
    Scenario: New cable TV (KAA) and KIP customer without self-install on NE4-VVO address
        Given a KDG service address where "analog and digital" TV is available with object category "NE4-VVO"
        And a KDG service address where internet with data transfer rate "1000" is available
        And self-install is 'not available'
        And a selection
            | productCode |
            | TC2         |
            | 01H:B06     |
        When I get the availability and basket
        Then the products have the states
            | productCode  | state         |
            | TC2          | selected      |
            | 01H:B06      | selected      |
            | TECNOKIP     | not available |
            | TECYESKIP    | not available |
            | TECNOTV      | not available |
            | TECYESTV     | not available |
            | VP0          | selectable    |
            | 1V1          | not available |
            | UMTECKIP:NOO | not available |
            | UMTECKIP:YES | not available | {code}
According to my understanding no kip technician is needed at VVO addresses since the TV technician will handle the installation.
As with the other bug tickets I think we need clarification from business what the expected behaviour is.

 ;;;

column919:
21/Sep/23 5:30 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;*Guess:* 
Cable product logic tries to rebuild the selection of the agent in each step. This means that certain clickflows are not really supported.

If their are for example two products A and B, A is visible, B is not, selecting A replaces A with B.
If the agent now selects A, A will be added to the selection and the product logic will replace it with B, the agent will see B in the selection.
If the cable product logic is executed again B is not a valid selection because it is not visible.

In this case A would be VP0, and B would be 1V1.

I do not think that there is a simple fix for this issue if my guess is correct.

The two options I see:
 # do not restrict the visibility of VP0 in this case
 ** this would imply that the agent could directly select VP0
 ** since VP0 and 1V1 are mapped to the same dropdown option in OSF -> the agent can only select VP0 together with 1V1, the replacement of 1V1 with VP0 then actually just removes 1V1 since VP0 is already selected.
 # maybe 1V1 should not be selectable in the first place
 ** instead of allowing the agent to select 1V1 which will automatically be replaced with VP0 allow the agent to select VP0 directly instead.

*Open questions:*

Which option is preferred by business?
 * if option 2 is preferred: should this also applied to other portals

What exactly are the affected cases? 
 * likely all test cases where the rule that replaces 1V1 with VP0 applies. 
 * Can business confirm that all cases affected by the rule below should be changed with either option 1 or 2?
 * The rule is: 

{code:java}
Rule 'Replace_1V1_with_VP0_when_ordering_KAI':
When
    selected products contain '1V1' and
    condition 'new_kip_order' applies and
    condition 'digitalSelected' applies
then
    deselect '1V1' and
    select 'VP0' with contract relation set to the main analog product. {code}
 ;;;

 * fill in the customer data
 * click on the button "Weiter"

20/Sep/23 4:07 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;This can be changed on cable side, but I am relatively sure that this was never implemented for Unity.

Without CR-716 the agent could select both "Anschluss ist bereits sehbereit" or "Anschluss ist nicht sehbereit" but only "Anschluss ist bereits sehbereit" would actually do anything (selecting a marker product).

10/Nov/23 12:34 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Hari Shankar Malviya added a comment - 
 
 
Hi [~shuyan.luo@vodafone.com]  ,

Based on the code investigation, it appears that this is not a issue, the manual_override_allowed field value is 0 in the catalog_package_subtypes table which is why its not allowing to deselect the hardware.

When the PCAT files are imported, the values of this field are set according to the values available in the PCAT files, so if the PCAT file does not contain this filed value for any stack, the value is considered to be 0.

When the manual_override_allowed field is set to 1 for a fixed stack, then the hardware can be deselected in the configurator according to the value in the manual_override_allowed field.

!image-2023-11-10-12-33-31-352.png!;;;

column926:
21/Sep/23 4:32 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;In order to properly fix this I assume that cable and OSF will have to deliver a fix.

According to the answer from [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-42115?focusedId=2910953&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-2910953 the display of the tv access details depends on the availability of the products TECNOTV and TECYESTV reported by the cable logic.

*Why does the workaround work?*

My *assumption* is that OSF remembers the availability of TECNOTV and/or TECYESTV from a previous execution of the cable logic.

If KIP is selected first, then the first executions of the cable product logic will return TECNOTV and TECYESTV as not available. 

If TV is selected first, then the first executions of the cable product logic will return either TECNOTV and/or TECYESTV as available.

-> This is something that has to be fixed by OSF

{*}What is the implication of the Workaround?{*}{*}{{*}}

Assuming cable product logic would return TECNOTV or TECYESTV as bookable the issue might persist in OSF, since as long as KIP is selected first TECNOTV and TECYESTV will still not be available from the start.

*Open questions from my perspective:*
 * which products exactly control the display of the tv access details in OSF?
 ** Is it only TECYESTV and TECNOTV or also products like VP0, 1V1?
 ** Is this controlled by special tags on products or categories, or are the products hardcoded in OSF?
Maybe [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] can answer this question?
 *  in which scenarios should which technician option be bookable in OSF?

 * 
 ** we have a list of ~80 test cases. Some of these are apparently not correct.
 ** Who can go through these test cases with us and determine which of them need to be changed?
 ** Without at least a contact person that can answer this question it will not make sense to start implementation of this ticket.

13/Jun/24 2:32 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;Hi all,
so, PORPDT-345 will not make this requirement obsolete, it will just slightly shift how it looks.

The new requirements are: if only TV is ordered, show the section. If TV + Internet is ordered, don't show it.

The new problem is this:
If the agent books the packages in the following order
 * TV
 * KIP

then the TV accessibility section is shown, but it should not.

The problem is still the same as described by [~simon.auch@vodafone.com] in the comment from 21/Sep/2023: 
OSF seems only to decide on whether to show the accessibility section for TV when the TV package is opened. So,
 * we first open TV and book a TV Connect ---> OSF sees that 1V1 and TECNOTV are available and correctly assumes that it should show the TV accessibility section
 * we then open the internet section and book some GigaZuhause tariff ---> from now on, 1V1 and TECNOTV are not available anymore, but OSF seems to not update its opinion on the TV accessibility and will display it anyway
 * IF the user just simply opens the TV package again (without changing anything), OSF updates again and will correctly NOT display it

This is something we cannot fix and still need a change from OSF.;;;

column955:
01/Jul/24 7:38 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;[~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] 
Thank you for the re-test.

The failure in case 2, where the technician option for KIP is wrongly displayed, is again the OSF bug discussed further below:
- when you book KIP first, then OSF calculates the technician option it wants to show for KIP, which is for a pure KIP order on an self-install address currently "Anschluss ist sehbereit".

- when you then book TV, it will not update the technician option it wants to show for KIP, and just show it regardless.

- when you just simply open the KIP package after the TV selection again, OSF _will_ update its opinion and not show the KIP technician section.

We cannot do anything here on our side and would need a fix from TechM side, so that OSF will always update both the TV and KIP technician section, no matter which package is currently opened.

 

About the "Verbindungsdaten speichern" field I don't know much unfortunately --neither how it is controlled nor what the desired logic behind it is.;;;
column957:
02/Jul/24 3:06 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;Hi, Ariadne,

{*}{color:#de350b}yes, I can confirm that in any case where we book KIP + TV (no matter if Broadvision or not, no matter which order we book it in), no technician section should be shown{color}{*}. 

The reason why this fails is as I tried to point out in my comment below. It really is pretty confusing, I apologize for that. I had a call with Natasa where I explained the problem, because it really is a bit hard to grasp.

So again in case of Broadvision what happens is:
 - [In the KIP package] KIP is booked, TV Connect is added because of Broadvision ---> OSF understands that no section for KIP should be shown because KIP + TV is booked and remembers that

 - [In the TV package] TV Digital is booked ---> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked

==> no KIP or TV technician section is shown

In case of Not-Broadvision:
 - [In the KIP package] Only KIP is booked, but not TV yet ----> OSF supposes that a technician section should be shown for KIP (because only KIP is booked) and remembers that
 - [In the TV package] TV Digital + TV Connect is booked ----> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked, but doesn't update the reasoning for KIP

==> technician section is shown for KIP, but not for TV;;;

column923:
18/Jan/23 8:21 PM;sukhdev.singh@vodafone.com;Hi [~arian.ghallaj@vodafone.com] ,

 

Please see the mail response from YairAharon on the same:

"Just to make the example of CUSTOMERID to be clear. Let’s use the following UM (test) data: legacy Customer-ID as 109235205 from the NRW region.

Based on the mapping defined in the confluence page, the CUSTOMERID is formatted as CUMST.UMREGION (region decode: 1= NRW ; 2= HSN ; 3= KBW) + CUMST.CUCNO (legacy Customer-ID).

So the CUSTOMERID identifier in MRT will have the value: {*}{color:#FF0000}1{color}{*}109235205 ."

[^FW_ MRT- UM identifiers.msg]

You need to add region code before the UM Customer Id.

[https://apigee-xtest03.rat-hub.citt.connect-vf.de/masterRoutingTable/v1/routing//{*}{color:#FF0000}1{color}{*}1003458101?id_type=CUSTOMERID|https://apigee-xtest03.rat-hub.citt.connect-vf.de/masterRoutingTable/v1/routing//1003458101?id_type=CUSTOMERID&market=NRW]

market is optional parameter.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave7.1 | ACC1&ACC2 | Telesales | Unitymedia orders with manual approval do not reach status completed
column41:
In case unitymedia order is not approved automatically in RNS, we are missing the order status and customer number in OSF.

Steps:
 * start order for unitymedia in Telesales (e.g. with KIP)
 * Submit order and check weborder ID in IAV
 * Identify reference ID is created in unity backend but order is not approved automatically
 * Approve order with the given reference ID in unitymedia backend (No new order is created! Weborder ID is set as external reference)
 * Check status / customer number in VKD and OGW -> information for customer ID is missing and status is not completed

Expected:

Also for manual approved orders the status is set to completed and customer ID is transferred via VKD to OSF

column992:
27/Nov/23 4:28 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;The discussion in the beginning of this defect and my understanding all the time:

In case order is auto approved, customer ID is immediately given back to VKD Gateway
In Case order is NOT auto approved but later manually, there is no new call to get the customer ID -> thats why its not available

07/Dec/23 1:51 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;Updates:

 

OGW needs the customer number in case Unity Manual Approval Orders in Telesales and Retails, which should be provided from VKD to OGW within the existing FulfillmentStarted Request.

 

The customer number is atm provided only for Auto Approval Orders, but missing for Manual Approval orders, therefore the document cannot be archived and the OGW processing remain in status pending (the VKD status is SUCCESS but the orders don't get Sucecss status in OSF Fronend):

An error was encountered while invoking ScanView-SaveDocument WS. Details [Error_Code: HTTPOutbound_0001, Error_Message: Received a fault from processing server for service '/ScanView-001/SaveDocument': An invalid number format or number value was encountered.

Note: Retail Manual Approval Orders don't have this issue because the call to oneDMS/Customernumber is not needed for the E2E flow. They get the Status Success.

 

As the customer number has not been sent for Manual Approval Order until now, a new PST change is required.

I will take the topic with me and check if we can request this change at the PST CAT train, Team Ash(Benjamin Sachse) or Nora.

 

The new requirement should contain following information:
 * no difference between retail and telesales from cable perspective
 * example set status messages received by OSF
 * fulfilment started from manual approval 
 * fulfilment started from automatic approval 


 * explanation on
 * what you clicked to create the manual approval order
 * how to approve the manual approval order

Will update here once it is clear how to process with the new change.;;;

It can be seen that the unity order tracker on the test2b does not trigger any more updates for the order after the one with the status OPEN (for which we already have a customer ID as seen in the log).

I checked the test2b database contains the UME_ORDER_STATUS 'COMPLETED', which is correct, but apparently not written by the unity order tracker. Maybe there is a race condition between the unity order tracker and some other service that tries to write this field? This would also explain why it only happens sometimes.;;;
